name: Poppy
about: Also known as That Poppy, she's a singer who gained popularity for her singles "Lowlife" and "Everybody Wants To Be Poppy." In 2017 she released her full-studio album titled Poppy.Computer; she also won the 2017 Streamy for Breakthrough Artist of the Year.

name: Acrello
about: Content creator who became widely recognized for his acrello account on TikTok. He's acquired over 6 million fans and more than 160 million Likes thanks in large part to his comedy bits and life hacks. He was previously known by the username justacrello until his account was hacked.

name: Shahid Khan
about: Known by his stage name Naughty Boy, he is a DJ and producer who released his debut album Hotel Cabana in 2013, featuring two top 10 singles titled "Wonder" and "La La La." In 2021, he appeared on the reality series I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here.

name: Verne Troyer
about: Actor and stuntman who rose to fame for his role as Mini-Me in the Austin Powers franchise. He also appeared in Men in Black and portrayed the Wee Waiter in Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas.

name: Celia Braud
about: American Instagram star who is best known for her lifestyle, fashion, and travel-related social media content. She also has a popular TikTok account featuring more lifestyle and dance videos.

name: Stunna 4 Vegas
about: Notable for his sometimes conversational flow, he is a hip hop artist notable for singles by the names of "Animal," "Hitn4" and "Punch Me In Pt. 3." Mixtapes of his include Stunna Season 2 and 4 Way or No Way.

name: Nikko Zingus
about: TikTok video sensation and Instagram influencer who has accrued more than 1.4 million fans for his nikkoz_ account on the former platform. He has posted a number of lip-sync, comedy and vlog content. He has been represented as a model by NEXT Models in Miami.

name: Crayator
about: Partnered Twitch broadcaster and personality who has streamed content from popular video games such as Skyrim, Overwatch, and Battlefield 1. He amassed a fan base of over 700,000 followers on the platform. He also became a member of the collaborative channel Click in 2018.

name: John Smith
about: English soldier, author, and explorer who was credited with the establishment of the first English settlement in North America.

name: Cole Hafers
about: Most well known for his lmfaoitscole TikTok account where he has over 460,000 fans. He is known for his pop and rap lip syncs on the platform, often utilizing the app's many effects in his videos.

name: Nia Lovelis
about: Along with her sister Rena, she became a member of the band Hey Violet and a host on the music network Revolt.tv. She has opened for some of her favorite bands, including The Smashing Pumpkins, Foo Fighters, Bush, Staind and Filter.

name: Diamond White
about: R&B and pop musician known for finishing fifth on the second season of the U.S. version of The X Factor. She provided her voice for the Nickelodeon animated series Pinky Malinky.

name: George Washington Carver
about: African-American scientist who became famous for his research into and promotion of alternative crops to cotton, such as peanuts, soybeans and sweet potatoes. The destruction of cotton crops by boll weevils inspired his scientific work, and he developed and promoted about 100 products made from peanuts that were useful for the house and farm, including cosmetics, dyes, paints, plastics, gasoline, and nitroglycerin.

name: Ssoyoung
about: Content creator on YouTube who combines ASMR and mukbang into satisfying videos. She has gained more than 6 million subscribers.

name: Kun
about: Vocalist and dancer making up one of the extended members of the SM Entertainment boy band NCT. He debuted with WayV in 2019.

name: Winter Kim
about: Pop singer and dancer who is best recognized as a member of the K-Pop group Aespa. The band is best recognized for their single "Black Mamba."

name: Angourie Rice
about: Most notable for her work on the silver screen, she starred in the film These Final Hours before landing parts in Walking with Dinosaurs, Nowhere Boys: The Book of Shadows and The Nice Guys.

name: Tank
about: Grammy Award-nominated R&B singer and producer who released albums like Now or Never. He has released singles like "Emergency" and "Sex Music."

name: Aidan Kohn-Murphy
about: Content creator who rose to fame on his aidanpleasestoptalking TikTok account, primarily for sharing both relatable and political videos to the platform. He has over 300,000 fans on the app.

name: Colin Morgan
about: Irish actor best known for playing the title role in the BBC series Merlin. He has also performed in several stage productions, including A Prayer For My Daughter and Shakespeare's The Tempest.

name: Jack Fowler
about: Soccer player and reality TV personality who gained fame by participating in the reality show Love Island. He has earned 1.4 million followers on Instagram.

name: Sophia La Corte
about: Trending dance, lip-sync, modeling and beauty content creator who rose to fame through the use of her sophialacorteee TikTok account. She has more than 600,000 followers on the platform.

name: Rumer Noel
about: Dancer who has worked with some of the biggest choreographers in Hollywood, from Tyce Diorio to Kenny Ortega. She has performed alongside stars like Katy Perry and Jon Secada and launched her own successful self-titled YouTube channel for dance choreography videos.

name: Morris Chestnut
about: Actor known for his role as Ricky in the Oscar-nominated film Boyz n the Hood. He also played Visitor Ryan on the alien reboot show V and Will Keaton in the NBC drama The Enemy Within.

name: Nyannyancosplay
about: Cosplaying sensation popular on the app TikTok where she posts lip-sync videos. She went viral for her lip-sync video where she sings iLOVEFRiDAY's "Mia Khalifa." She has accrued more than 1.5 million fans.

name: Caryn Marjorie
about:
Known in the digital world as cutiecaryn, she is a social media star who first gained a following in 2016 for her YouNow broadcasts, where she would frequently interact with her fans.
In 2018, she expanded into YouTube, where she is well known for her vlogs, storytimes, and comedic videos. She has amassed over 750,000 subscribers.

name: Erika Saccone
about: Famous for her YouTube makeup tutorials and other popular posts, this Irish web star has over 190,000 subscribers. Also popular on Instagram, she has accumulated more than 180,000 followers.

name: Betsy Ross
about: Seamstress who is credited with sewing the first American flag. A bridge that connects Pennsylvania and New Jersey is named the Betsy Ross Bridge in her honor.

name: Nextraker
about: Content creator specializing in pranks, hacks, cheats and more on YouTube. Some of his most watched prank videos include "How To Pull Off The Nastiest Prank On Your RoomMate!" and "The Frozen Mentos Prank," helping him earn over 2 million subscribers.

name: Eiichiro Oda
about: Popular Japanese manga artist who was best known for his work on the One Piece series, which became the highest-selling manga series of all time, with more than 490 million copies in circulation. He was voted the fifth most popular manga artist in Japan.

name: Axel Auriant
about: Actor who began playing Lucas on the French version of the Norwegian drama series Skam in 2018. He had previously appeared on shows like Nos Chers Voisins and in feature films like Jamais Contente (2016).

name: DPR Live
about: South Korean rap artist whose name of DPR Live stands for Dream Perfect Regime. Some of his top singles include "Know Me," "God Bless" and "Right Here Right Now."

name: Alexis Painter
about: Lip sync, dance, and couple content creator who rose to fame through the use of her ap.baby TikTok account. Her popularity on the platform led to her amassing more than 80,000 followers.

name: Mr. Lawrence
about: Voice actor and writer who is best known as the voice of Plankton on Nickelodeon's SpongeBob SquarePants.

name: Daniel Haye
about: Otherwise known as Deej Design, Daniel "DJ" Haye is a YouTube vlogger known for his comedic vlogs, varied challenge videos, and occasional heated rants posted to more than 500,000 dedicated subscribers.

name: Chance Strive
about: Conversational TikTok content creator known for posting relatable videos in which he discusses relationships and women. His popularity on the platform has led to him amassing more than 1.2 million fans on his chance_strive account.

name: Maura Gallagher
about: Birth mother of One Direction superstar Niall Horan and Greg Horan.

name: SoaR Milo
about: Social media star and gamer who is best recognized for the comedic Fortnite and Call of Duty videos he posts to his SoaR Milo YouTube channel. His content has earned him over 700,000 subscribers on the platform.

name: Sonta Me'Shay
about: Singer and actress who has released songs like "Friends?," "MMMM" and "All I Want is You."

name: Dawid Kwiatkowski
about: Polish singer who gained a substantial following with albums like 2013's 9893 and 2014's Pop & Roll. In 2014, he won awards for Best Polish Act and Best Eastern European Act at the MTV Europe Music Awards. He later appeared on Dancing With The Stars in Poland, placing third.

name: Junior Villegas
about: Comedy content creator on TikTok known for sharing relatable couples and family skits on his fknjunior account. He has more than 1.7 million enthusiastic fans on the platform. He has gained a following of over 60,000 on his jr_villegas1 Instagram account.

name: Donia Samir Ghanem
about: Film actress known appearing in popular Egyptian films like Teer enta and 365 Days of Happiness. She's also had roles in television series like Ahzan Mariam and Al Kabeer. She also served as a judge on the Arabic version of The X Factor in 2015.

name: Paul Revere
about: Patriot of the American Revolution who warned his fellow patriots, during his legendary midnight ride, that the British were coming.

name: Chapati Hindustani Gamer
about: Hindi gaming commentator who provided comedic takes while playing Minecraft, Grand Theft Auto V, Paladins, PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds, Fortnite and other games. He has earned more than 7 million subscribers.

name: Lauren Silverman
about: New York-based social climber who gained massive fame for having a child with entrepreneur and American Idol judge Simon Cowell.

name: Brian Hartwig
about: American photographer who is best known for his popular videography and photography work with well known social media influencers like Twan Kuyper and Brent Rivera. He has his own production studios called B-Hart Studios.

name: Ahmedddd_
about: Relatable video creator who has posted comedy in addition to content about being Muslim. He is also known as Hamody the Iraqi and has earned more than 270,000 followers for his TikTok account.

name: DT Studios
about: Teen YouTube sensation who has gone viral with his fidget spinner and Pokemon card-related videos. He has more than 80,000 subscribers. One of his mail day Pokemon card opening videos has gained over 5.3 million views.

name: Colby Brock
about: Gained fame on Vine as one half of the video content creating duo Sam and Colby alongside his friend Sam Golbach. They then transitioned to YouTube, where they have earned over 5 million subscribers. They primarily explore haunted houses and other scary locations for their YouTube videos. Colby also has his own self-titled YouTube channel where he posts additional horror and scary content.

name: Tfue
about: Professional skimboarder who is a partnered Twitch live streamer, earning more than 10 million followers to his Tfue Twitch channel, which was the 8th most watched Twitch channel in 2018. He was a member of the highly successful FaZe Clan for about a year from 2018 to 2019.

name: Bryson Tiller
about: Kentucky singer and rapper who, at 15 years old, began writing and recording his own music. He became notable for his debut single titled "Don't," which peaked at 13 on the Billboard Hot 100. His debut studio album Trapsoul also reached number eight on the Billboard 200.

name: Brianna Paige Arsement
about: Registered nurse who is most famous for her relationship with popular YouTube gamer Preston Arsement. Her own Brianna YouTube channel has accrued more than 6 million subscribers. She has singing and acting experience, having starred in stage musicals like Legally Blonde.

name: Kane Tanaka
about: Supercentenarian who became the verified oldest living person by the Gerontology Research Group in the world in July 2018 upon the death of Chiyo Miyako. She was validated as the world's oldest living person at age 115.

name: Jennifer Tran
about: Popular social media personality known by the username thailiian who is best known for her Instagram account, which has over 340,000 followers. She has run her own beauty company called Exotiic Boutique.

name: Shelley Hennig
about: Portrayed Stephanie Johnson on the soap opera Days of Our Lives and was cast as Malia Tate in Teen Wolf. She also starred in the series The Secret Circle as Diana Meade and she has played starring roles in the horror films Ouija and Unfriended.

name: Ben Hardy
about: Became known for his role as Peter Beale on the long-running British soap opera EastEnders. His breakout film role came in 2016 in X-Men: Apocalypse. In 2018, he starred as Roger Taylor in Bohemian Rhapsody.

name: Jilly Anais
about: Rising pop artist with a debut single called "The Juice," which was a part of her debut EP of the same name. The EP was co-written and produced by the LA Production duo The Invaders.

name: caitibugzz
about: TikTok star famous for posting lip-sync videos. Her caitibugzz account has gained 290,000 followers and 3.8 million likes. She also posts on her twitch.caitibugzz account, where she has amassed over 70,000 followers. She has also sold her own hoodies and mugs on the Merch Gardens website.

name: River Bleu
about: Web star and actress who appeared in an episode of Sam & Cat in 2014. She has amassed more than 110,000 followers to her riverbleu7 Instagram account. She was previously popular on Vine, earning over 70,000 followers on the 6-second video app. She has been represented by the NCA Talent Agency for acting.

name: Danny Miller
about: Most famous for his role as Aaron Livesy on the popular British soap opera Emmerdale, Miller is also notable for his series regular roles on Lightfields and Scott and Bailey.

name: Mishovy Silenosti
about: Czech YouTube personality who is widely known for his self-titled channel. He has garnered popularity there for his original pop culture and gaming-related songs, including "CZECH MINECRAFT SONG!!!," which has earned more than 4 million views. He has also posted a number of music videos for his original songs.

name: Biz Betzing
about: Internet personality, model and actress who has posted photos from her photo shoots on her self-titled Instagram account. She was featured in the HBO hit series Shameless and has modeled for companies like Banjanan.

name: Bridger Nelson
about: Member of the large Nelson family that is featured on the YouTube channel Not Enough Nelsons. His family channel is home to videos such as "School MORNING ROUTINE with a Large Family of 18! + Giveaway!!!" and "HANDCUFFED To Our CRUSHES For 24 HOURS!!"

name: Jacob Green
about: Curly haired TikTok personality who is recognized for sharing POV, transition, duet, and text-on-screen videos. He has built a fanbase of more than 500,000 followers on his jjacobgreenn account.

name: Renee Elise Goldsberry
about: Actress who rose to fame through her role as Evangeline Williamson on the long-running soap opera One Life to Live. She's perhaps best known for originating the role of Angelica Schuyler Church in Broadway's Hamilton. Her other broadway credits include The Color Purple, Rent, and The Lion King.

name: Claire Rosinkranz
about: Social media star and singer who posts her experimental blues pop original music to her clairerosinkranz TikTok account. Her videos have earned her over 600,000 followers on the video platform.

name: Taye Diggs
about: Actor known for starring in films such as Rent, How Stella Got Her Groove Back and Set It Up. In 2018, he began starring in The CW's All American. Other notable works include, Chicago, Cake, Days of Wrath, and The Wood.

name: Henwy
about: Popular YouTube star best known for his Henwy channel where he posts gaming videos. He often posts videos about Minecraft and Fortnite.

name: Atis Paul
about: Lifestyle, vlog and couples content creator who rose to fame through the use of his self-titled TikTok account. He has more than 500,000 fans and 380,000 likes on the platform.

name: Nadia Zuniga
about: POV content creator and TikTok personality who rose to fame by sharing a variety of lip sync performances. Her popularity on the platform has led to her amassing more than 3.8 million followers.

name: Dax Shepard
about: Actor who became known for portraying Crosby Braverman on NBC's Parenthood and for his roles in the films Without a Paddle, Let's Go to Prison, Zathura and Employee of the Month. He also hosts the podcast Armchair Expert.

info.birthplace: San Pedro de Macoris | Dominican Republic

name: Fernando Tatís Jr.
about: Professional baseball player who is recognized for having played the shortstop position for the San Diego Padres MLB team. He made his debut with the organization after being named on the Opening Day roster.

name: Alex Ramos
about: Versatile talent who became most well known for his Vine account, which earned over 1 million followers. He also produces electronic music. He has over 120,000 followers on his sorryimalex Instagram account and more than 90,000 subscribers on his self-titled YouTube channel.

name: Dylan Mitchell
about: Instagram and YouTube personality with more than 220,000 followers on the former network. He frequently makes videos with YouTube sensation Tanner Braungardt.

name: Nicolette Waltzer
about: DIY slime creator found on the enormously popular Instagram account glitter.slimes, where she showcases the slime she would make available for purchase. She would earn more than 1.7 million followers.

name: Alden Richards
about: GMA network star of Alakdana who earned a 2011 Golden Screen Award for Best New Actor. He has played a leading role in such series as Alakdana and Tween Hearts. He has also appeared on the variety shows Sunday PinaSaya and Eat Bulaga!

name: Dana Vaughns
about: Pop singer best known for his time with the boy band IM5. He had his first big break in 2009 when he appeared in Hannah Montana: The Movie.

name: Vinn Sander
about: Television and film actor who is recognized for his work on the mini-series Dhar Mann. In 2019, he appeared in the feature film Fear and Desire. He has amassed more than 120,000 Instagram followers.

name: Ian Connor
about: Model and style entrepreneur self-proclaimed as The King of the Youth who became a member of the A$AP Crew as an influential fashion and street culture personality.

name: Gigiitheblackbarbie
about: Short-form content creator on TikTok who is known for sharing fashion videos on her gigiitheblackbarbie account. She has more than 3.6 million followers on the platform.

name: Miller Wilson
about: Wildlife enthusiast with a highly successful, self-titled YouTube channel who puts himself in life threatening situations for the good of his 1.2 million subscribers. He catches animals with his bare hands and sometimes captures, cooks and eats them.

name: Nilsa Prowant
about: Reality television personality who rose to fame after being cast on MTV's Floribama Shore in 2017. She has gone on to amass more than 850,000 followers on her nilsaprowant Instagram account.

name: Cuba Gooding Jr.
about: Actor who won an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role as football player Rod Tidwell in the film Jerry Maguire. His other credits include As Good As it Gets, Men of Honor, Red Tails and Norbit. He stars as OJ Simpson on the FX series The People v. O. J. Simpson: American Crime Story.

name: Sylvia Chan
about: YouTube content creator of short films, music videos, comedy skits, and more. She worked alongside her ex-husband, Ryan Tan, as part of an independent filmmaking group called Night Owl Cinematics. Their "11 Reasons Why Singaporeans Complain!" video was a 2013 Singapore Most Trending YouTube Video.

name: Cole Caufield
about: Hockey forward who finished as the 2020 Big Ten Scoring Champion while playing for the University of Wisconsin Badgers. He was also the Big Ten Freshman of the Year after being selected 15th overall by the Montreal Canadiens in the 2019 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Kate Bosworth
about: Blue Crush actress who debuted in The Horse Whisperer. She also starred in Young Americans and Wonderland.

name: Scribblejuice
about: YouTube star who is famous for her Scribblejuice channel. She has gained popularity there for her original animations based on her own cartoon illustrative work.

name: Mandy Harvey
about: American jazz singer who rose to fame on the hit reality competition show America's Got Talent. She lost her hearing at the age of 18 but continued to pursue her passion and traveled as a jazz soloist and a motivational speaker.

name: Marcus Perez
about: Instagram star who was also popular on Vine for his beatboxing skills. He has more than 1.2 million followers on Instagram, where he continues to upload beatboxing videos.

name: Bridget Williams
about: Movie actress who played the daughter in A Night of Horror Volume 1 in 2015. She is also a model and she is popular on Instagram with over 600,000 followers.

name: LJ Benet
about: Known for his recurring role of Karl Fink on the series Dog with a Blog, he landed a supporting role in the film Dark Skies and played the part of Danny Zigwitz in the Sundance Film Festival honorable mention jury award short The Legend of Beaver Dam.

name: Deaken Bluman
about: American TV actor who is well known for his role as Winston in 13 Reasons Why. He has also appeared in Fall Into Me and First Love.

name: Authenticteecee
about: Short-form comedy content creator and TikTok personality who rose to fame by sharing hilarious vignettes on her self-titled account. She boasts more than 4 million followers on the platform.

name: Sheree Whitfield
about: Reality Star known for her appearance on the Bravo show The Real Housewives of Atlanta. She started the now defunct She by Sheree clothing line.

name: London Charles
about: Born Chandra Davis, she is a model and singer who gained national reality fame by winning VH1's Flavor of Love 2.

name: Ghost Ex
about: Gamer primarily known for posting Fortnite content. He has earned more than 600,000 subscribers. He has also been known as CallMeEx and ChronicEx.

name: Sabre Norris
about: Professional surfer and skateboarder who went viral on YouTube as the 1st Australian female and 3rd female in history to land a 540 on a half pipe. She became the 2nd youngest surfer to compete in a World Surf League event as a wildcard at the Sydney International Pro. She stars alongside her siblings on the YouTube channel The Norris Nuts.

name: Vy Qwaint
about: YouTube content creator who has made fictional videos about Project Zorgo for more than 11 million subscribers. She previously uploaded fashion, beauty and lifestyle content, sharing hack and DIY videos.

name: Florence Pugh
about: Actress who starred in the 2019 films Midsommar and Little Women. She made her film debut in the 2014 feature The Falling and also appeared as Katherine in the 2016 drama Lady Macbeth. She was cast in the murder/mystery film The Maid.

name: Jisoo Kim
about: One of four members of the South Korean girl group Black Pink, which released the album Square One in August of 2016. She has appeared on television in the shows The Producers and Inkigayo.

name: Lincoln Markham
about: Star of the YouTube channel What's Inside?'s collection of videos. He has gained popularity there, alongside his father Daniel, for exploring the insides of a wide variety of objects, including athletic equipment, toilets, and LED shoes.

name: Greta Thunberg
about: Swedish activist who has gained prominence for her work to halt climate change and global warming. She rose to fame for organizing the world's first school strike for climate outside Sweden's parliament in August 2018. She gave a speech at the 2019 United Nations Climate Action Summit, berating world leaders for not taking more actions against climate change.

name: Alec Maternowski
about: TikTok star known for his lip-sync videos. He has amassed more than 650,000 followers on his curlierfuq account. Multiple TikTok videos of his have featured content about twins and have included his twin brother.

name: Runik
about: Social media star and musician who is most popular on Instagram, where he has more than 1.8 million followers. In 2017, he was diagnosed with diffuse large B cell lymphoma and set up a Go Fund Me to cover his chemotherapy treatments.

name: Frimzy
about: Social star also known as ayefrimzy who has earned over 1.1 million fans on TikTok. He gained his following on the platform by posting lip-syncs primarily to rap and pop songs by such artists as PartyNextDoor and Usher.

name: Brianni Walker
about: One of the stars of Brat's hit web series Mani, she is a versatile entertainer who would add reporter, co-host, correspondent, model, rapper and dancer to her arsenal before she even became a teenager. She booked minor parts for shows and movies including Sam & Cat, Insecure, Captain Underpants and Ben Affleck's Live By Night. She has been nominated for multiple Young Entertainers & Young Artist Awards.

name: Raegan Revord
about: Child actress known for her recurring role as Megan on the ABC sitcom Modern Family and as Missy Cooper on CBS's The Big Bang Theory Spinoff, Young Sheldon. She also guest starred on a 2016 episode of the Netflix series Grace and Frankie.

name: George Janko
about: Recording artist with a debut album called Without Fame who became popular on both YouTube and Vine. He has earned over 1.5 million subscribers to his self-titled YouTube channel, where he posts comedy videos such as sketches and challenges.

name: Erick Brian Colón
about: One-fourth of the boy band CNCO who was selected as the fourth member of the group after competing on the reality competition show La Banda.

name: Chandler Alexis
about: Fashion and beauty enthusiast partnered with Style Haul who shares "story time," challenge, and prank videos on her channel in addition to fashion and beauty content. She became very popular on YouTube under the user name LushBarbiee, earning over 750,000 subscribers to her channel.

name: Mimi Faust
about: Born Oluremi James, she is best known as a star on the VH1 reality series Love & Hip Hop: Atlanta.

name: Eli Manning
about: NFL quarterback who was named MVP of Super Bowls XLII and XLVI while leading the New York Giants to victory over the New England Patriots on both occasions. He was selected first overall by the San Diego Chargers in 2004, then traded directly to the Giants. He is the younger brother of fellow Super Bowl MVP Peyton Manning.

name: Mel Gibson
about: Directed and starred in the 1995 film Braveheart, which won the Academy Award for Best Picture. His best known roles as an actor include Martin Riggs in the Lethal Weapon series and the title character in the Mad Max series. He also starred in The Patriot and directed the critically-acclaimed films Apocalypto and Hacksaw Ridge.

name: Katie McGrath
about: Irish model and actress who rose to stardom through her role on BBC's Merlin from 2008 to 2012. She appeared in NBC's Dracula from 2013 until 2014 and in The CW's Supergirl, beginning in 2016. She was also cast as Zara Young in the 2015 feature Jurassic World.

name: N&A Productions
about: YouTube star best known as N&A Productions for his challenge, prank and trick shot videos. He's amassed over 3 million subscribers as well as 461 million views and counting. He has also become a boxer, fighting in multiple publicized matches.

name: Zeddywill
about: Popular social media star also known as CBANDZZZ who gained popularity for his "window talk" comedy series that he posts to his zeddywill TikTok account. His videos have earned him over 5 million followers on the platform. He has been known for his unique style of fast talking POV videos.

name: Xai Rivera
about: Creator for TikTok who has earned more than 17 million likes for his xai.x.riveraaa account.

name: Les Do Makeup
about: Instagram star who is known for posting both a mix of modeling content and makeup related content to her over 1.8 million Instagram followers. Her makeup work often focuses on eyeliner as well as a variety of shades of makeup as well. Her Les Do Makeup merchandise shop has sold a variety of comfortable clothing items.

name: The Card Guy
about: Magician who has found massive success on TikTok for sharing his expertise. His short magic trick and illusion clips often in public and with fellow social media stars like Kevin Perry have helped him grow to more than 16 million fans.

name: Olivia Buckland
about: ITV2 reality television personality who would star in the second series of the dating show Love Island. She finished the show as a runner-up alongside Alex Bowen.

name: Kiwiz
about: YouTube personality who is particularly known for his gaming content, including his Call of Duty trick shot video series. He has also served as a content director for the YouTube gaming and eSports organization Red Reserve and later Obey Alliance.

name: Goo Hara
about: K-pop singer and dancer who performed with the all-girl group KARA. Also an actress, she starred on the TV series City Hunter.

name: Michael Schumacher
about: Champion Formula One race car driver who represented Ferrari from 1996 to 2006.

name: Darius Rusnack
about: Challenge, comedy and lip-sync video creator on the platform TikTok where he has accrued more than 1.1 million fans to his dariussnack account.

name: Emiru
about: American gamer who is known primarily for streaming League of Legends on Twitch. She has earned more than 600,000 followers to her emiru account.

name: Michael Jaroh
about: Gymnast who won the still rings portion of the 2018 Men's Junior Olympic National Championships, and finished 3rd overall. He also finished in 3rd place on the pommel horse at the 2018 U.S. Gymnastics Championships.

name: CJ
about: Rapper who is known for his breakout single "Whoopty," which was released in 2020. Cardi B filmed herself rapping along to the viral hit.

name: Tamia M. Whittaker
about: Head co-captain of the Dancing Dolls in 2015-2016 who stars on the Lifetime reality series Bring It! She also became a member of the Purple Diamonds dance team.

name: Angel Espinal
about: POV video creator as well as fan-engaging vlogger who has earned his following on TikTok. He has accrued more than 850,000 fans for his angel_espinal account.

name: Dawood Savage
about: Comedy content creator and social media personality who rose to fame by sharing a variety of skits on his dawoodees Instagram account. He has earned more than 10,000 followers on the platform. He has also grown his DawoodSAVAGE YouTube channel to over 1 million followers.

name: Lloyd Polite
about: Smooth-voiced R&B singer who released the gold-certified album Street Love in 2007. He has released singles like "You" and "Get it Shawty."

name: Vicky Logan
about: YouTuber whose beauty and fashion tips, as seen in popular videos like "Full Face Routine: Long Lasting Makeup + Acne Scar Coverage," have earned her a dedicated fan base. Her channel has accumulated more than 360,000 subscribers.

name: Trixie Hyde
about: English child actress who is best known for having been cast as Sybil Hallow on the CBBC series The Worst Witch. This exposure led to her building a social media fan base.

name: Candelaria Molfese
about: Argentine actress and singer who has played the role of Camila on the Disney Channel series Violetta.

name: Danica McKellar
about: Played Winnie Cooper on the television series The Wonder Years. In 2015, she appeared as the character The Quail in the TV mini-series Project MC2.

name: Tess Krauser
about: Lip-sync, dance and couples content creator who is widely recognized for her tesskrauser TikTok account. She has garnered more than 850,000 followers and over 18 million likes on the platform.

name: Taylor King
about: Music producer and YouTube personality who is recognized for sharing hip-hop beats on his self-titled YouTube channel. He has made music similar to songs produced for J Cole and Drake.

name: Jung Da-won
about: Most well known as the sister of BTS member J-Hope. She has grown quite popular on social media, earning more than 9 million Instagram followers to her mejiwoo103 account.

name: Bella Wylie
about: Chef who became the champion of Chopped Junior season two at the age of 15.

name: Holly Auna

name: Hilaria Thomas Baldwin
about: Became known as the wife of megastar Alec Baldwin. She has appeared frequently on numerous talk shows and at entertainment events. She appeared on an episode of the series Nightcap in 2017.

name: Scarlet May
about: Short-form content creator on TikTok who is recognized for sharing lip sync performances and skits featuring American sign language. Her popularity on the platform has led to her amassing more than 5 million followers.

name: John Smith
about: Cardiff-based tattooist who gained a television audience appearing on the MTV reality show Just Tattoo of Us.

name: Yasmin Galvão
about: YouTube star who has gained fame for her self-titled channel. She has garnered popularity for her kid-friendly brand of vlogging, which has included slime making, school hauls and routines, study tips, and personal adventures.

name: Luke Eich
about: YouTube star who is famous for his self-titled channel. He has gained massive popularity for his extreme sport and adventure vlogging as a skateboarder. He also collaborates with his friend Kelly Wakasa on the YouTube channel LIFE OF LUKE AND KELLY.

name: Weston Koury
about: Comedic social media personality who is best known for his humorous posts on Instagram and YouTube, earning over 1.1 million followers and more than 650,000 subscribers on the respective networks. He and his sister teamed up to run the Sinjin Drowning YouTube channel. His new song "georgenotfound onlyfans" is a hit on a large number of platforms.

name: Blue Ivy Carter
about: Famous first child of superstars Beyonce and Jay-Z. Her parents tried to trademark her name in order to start a merchandise line.

name: Clix
about: Video game player who signed with Misfits Gaming, and later NRG Esports. He was a 5x World Cup Qualifier as a Fortnite player and took home first place at the WC 2019 NAE Qualifiers - Week 9 in June of 2019. He won another tournament, and $10,000, in July of 2019.

name: Sofia Wylie
about: Actress and dancer who played the character Buffy on the Disney series Andi Mack. She earned a recurring role as June on the series Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn and in 2018, she made her film debut in Louise Alston's Back of the Net. She was also cast as Gina in the High School Musical reboot High School Musical: The Musical: The Series.

name: Lewis Hamilton
about: British Formula One race car driver regarded as one of the best in the history of the sport. He won F1 championships in 2008, 2014, 2015, 2017, 2018, 2019, and 2020, setting a record for most race victories by a British driver. He became the first black driver to ever compete in F1.

name: Jeremy Renner
about: Earned an Academy Award nomination for Best Actor for his role as Sgt. First Class William James in The Hurt Locker. He has also played prominent parts in such films as The Bourne Legacy, Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation, S.W.A.T., and The Town.

name: Mia Dinoto
about: Social star and gymnast who has amassed over 500,000 subscribers to her YouTube channel through a range of videos including tutorials, DIY videos, reaction videos, slime videos and more. She is a friend and occasional collaborator of the fellow gymnasts from Gymscool.

name: Mini Ladd
about: YouTube star with over 5 million subscribers on his Mini Ladd channel. He frequently posts videos of funny video game moments such as his popular video GTA 5 Online Funny Moments. One of his most popular videos, "TRY NOT TO LAUGH CHALLENGE!! - OFFENSIVE MEME COMPILATION!", has received over 12.4 million views.

name: Nicolas Cage
about: Longtime actor who won the Academy Award for Best Actor in 1995 for his role in Leaving Las Vegas. He has also starred in such films as Gone in 60 Seconds, The Rock, National Treasure, Adaptation and Kick-Ass.

name: Mully
about: Australian content creator who acquired over 100,000 YouTube subscribers on his Mully channel in its first 2 months of existence. His humorous VR gaming videos have since been viewed a combined 617 million times. His "daycare is cancelled" video has received over 19.4 million times since it was released in May of 2020.

name: Lamar Jackson
about: Dynamic quarterback who was a unanimous selection as 2019 NFL MVP after a historic season with the Baltimore Ravens. He was the 2016 Heisman Trophy winner at Louisville and was selected 32nd overall in the 2018 NFL Draft by the Ravens.

name: Eden Hazard
about: Belgian winger who joined Chelsea in 2012. A year earlier, he became the youngest player ever to win the UNFP Ligue 1 Player of the Year award as a member of France's Lille OSC. He debuted with Belgium's national team in 2008 and later became their captain. In 2019, he'd sign with Real Madrid.

name: Robert Sheehan
about: Gained recognition for his role as Nathan Young in Misfits and was featured in the play The Playboy of the Western World. He also played Luke in Cherrybomb and starred in Killing Bono and Mortal Engines. In 2019, he landed the role of Klaus Hargreeves in Netflix's The Umbrella Academy.

name: Camille Rowe
about: French model notable for her appearances in advertising campaigns for Chloe, Gap, and Victoria's Secret. She is also well known as a cover model for Elle, Marie Claire, and Vogue Paris.

name: Nunu Nellz
about: Rapper known for being a part of the Ultimate Rap League. She is also a co-host for Battle Rap Arena. Early in her career, she followed Drake's tours around the country.

name: Lauren Cohan
about: American-born English actress who had her major breakout role as Maggie Greene on the AMC series The Walking Dead. She later starred as Greta Evans in the 2016 film The Boy. In 2019, she began starring in ABC's Whiskey Cavalier.

name: DennisASMR
about: Video creator on YouTube who specializes in ASMR content to help his 1 million subscribers relax and sleep. He has used many props in his videos, such as sponges and steel wool, to make his soothing sounds.

name: Mary-Kate Cooper
about: Web star who has earned over 950,000 fans on her marykatecooper TikTok account as well as more than 210,000 subscribers on YouTube. She has been known on social media as Officially MK. She is the cousin of the stars of the Bratayley YouTube channel.

name: Jinxx
about: Born Jeremy Miles Ferguson, he is a guitarist, pianist, and violinist who plays rhythm guitar for the goth rock band Black Veil Brides.

name: Jessica Darrow
about: Actress known for her role in Encanto. She uses her jessdarrow_ Instagram account to share snapshots from her personal life and promotional info for upcoming work projects. She has accrued 1,000 followers.

name: Juan Gabriel
about: Legendary Mexican singer and composer whose album Recuerdos II became the best-selling album of all-time in Mexico. He released more than 40 albums throughout his career and wrote over 1,800 songs. He's best known for classic hits like "Así Fue," "Hasta que Te Conocí," "Querida" and "Amor Eterno," among many others.

name: Vybz Kartel
about: Reggae and dancehall artist known for the singles "Turn & Wine" and "Romping Shop." In 2014, he was sentenced to life in prison for murder.

name: Stormie Goldsmith
about: Social media starlet who is famous for her stormiegoldsmithh Instagram account. She has gained massive popularity there for her personal lifestyle, beach, and bikini modeling photoblogging.

name: Lauryn Thompson
about: Also known as Pumpkin, she is the older sister of Alana "Honey Boo Boo" Thompson who became famous on TLC's Here Comes Honey Boo Boo.

name: Leslie Grace
about: Latin Grammy Award-nominated artist whose self-titled 2013 album rose to #4 on the Billboard Latin Albums chart. The album was nominated for a Latin Grammy for Best Contemporary Tropical Album.

name: Lauren Curtis
about: Top Australian YouTube fashion and beauty guru known for her channel laurenbeautyy, where she posts makeup and hair tutorials, product reviews, and all things beauty-related. She has over 3.3 million subscribers. She's also popular on Instagram, with more than 1.3 million followers.

name: Rebecca Felgate
about: English blogger known for running her self-titled blog, which covers topics like food and theatre. She's also been a presenter for the YouTube channels Inform Overload and Most Amazing Top Ten.

name: Børns
about: Musician named Garrett Borns, but best known by the stage name Børns. His debut album Dopamine was released in 2015. The album features the hit singles "10,000 Emerald Pools" and "Electric Love."

name: Raymond Warner
about: American scooter rider who has ridden for Epic Scooters as well as Envy Scooters. He is a popular presence on YouTube, attracting more than 1.2 million subscribers to his channel, where he documents his adventures in professional scooter riding.

name: Aloe Blacc
about: American soul singer who released the gold-certified album Good Things in 2010. His best known singles include "I Need a Dollar" and "Loving You Is Killing Me."

name: Kade Knight
about: Nicknamed Lil Sperry, He is a TikTok video creator who has showcased his athleticism in addition to posting more classic videos on the platform. He has earned more than 850,000 fans.

name: Marcus Scribner
about: Landed his breakthrough role as Andre Johnson, Jr. on the ABC sitcom Black-ish.

name: Dustin Diamond
about: Actor and comedian known best for his role as Screech on the hit show Saved by the Bell.

name: HighDistortion
about: Twitch broadcaster and personality who is known for creating and streaming content from the co-op sandbox survival video game Fortnite. He has amassed more than 1.5 million followers on his highdistortion channel.

name: Ethan Matthews
about: Lip-sync content creator who rose to fame by sharing performances and flirty messages on his itsethanmatthews TikTok account. He has more than 320,000 dedicated followers on the platform.

name: Bway Yungy
about: Rapper and hip-hop recording artist who is best known for songs such as "Sin Again," "Trap Talk," and "Message Sent." His popularity led to him amassing more than 320,000 followers on Instagram.

name: Kerri Medders
about: Singer turned actress who became well known for the release of her self-titled album in January 2012, she followed it up with singles in March and July 2015. She plays the character Gwenny on the Netflix series Alexa & Katie and Emma Hayes on SEAL Team.

name: Amalie Olsen
about: YouTube vlogger who is known for her self-titled channel's content. She has gained popularity there for her comedic videos.

name: Nika Motiie
about: Vlogger and creative editor on TikTok whose nikamotiie account would attract more than 340,000 fans.

name: Annabelle Gesson
about: Variety content creator on TikTok who rose to fame with her annabellegesson account. Her videos have received more than 85 million likes on the platform.

name: Hardwell
about: Hugely successful DJ who was ranked as DJ Magazine's #1 DJ on the Top 100 list in 2013.

name: Brett Dalton
about: He starred as Agent Grant Ward on the television series Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. in 2013. That same year, he also played Robert Todd Lincoln in the TV film Killing Lincoln.

name: Marcel Somerville
about: English reality television personality who rose to fame after appearing as a contestant on the ITV series Love Island. He landed the opportunity to appear on the show through a meeting set up by his agent.

name: Irrfan Khan
about: Indian leading man who became known for his roles in the 2012 international hit Life of Pi and the 2008 Academy Award winner Slumdog Millionaire. He also played Rajit Ratha in the 2012 blockbuster The Amazing Spider-Man and Simon Masrani in 2015's Jurassic World.

name: Nadine Leopold
about: Austrian Victoria's Secret model who dated One Direction star Harry Styles from late 2014 to early 2015. In 2018, she began starring on E!'s docu-series Model Squad.

name: Millard Fillmore
about: The 13th president of the United States, as well as the last Whig to be president, who entered office upon the death of his predecessor, Zachary Taylor.

name: HerNameCece
about: Member of the dance crew KidGoalss whose YouTube videos of routines set to "JuJu On The Beat" and "Get LiT" have each surpassed 1 million views. Her dance partners are her cousin J'Den and her younger sister Chevy.

name: Kenny Loggins
about: Singer-songwriter who was popular in the 1980s with such hit singles as "Danger Zone" and "Footloose." He also performed with Jim Messina in the band Loggins and Messina.

name: Elvis Presley
about: Known as "The King of Rock n' Roll," he rose to prominence in the late 1950s, becoming a legendary presence in cultural history and the best-selling solo artist in the history of pop. He released such #1 singles as "Hound Dog," "Jailhouse Rock," and "Stuck on You."

name: Noah Cyrus
about: Actress, singer, songwriter, and younger sister of Miley Cyrus. She played Gracie Herbert on the TV series Doc and appeared on Hannah Montana from 2006 to 2010. She also provided the voice of the main character in the animated Hayao Miyazaki fantasy adventure film Ponyo. As a singer, she released her debut single "Make Me (Cry)" featuring Labrinth in 2016.

name: Valkyrae
about: Gamer who is primarily known for posting gameplay from Among Us, Minecraft and Fortnite to her Valkyrae YouTube channel, which has amassed over 3.6 million subscribers. She first found a web following on Twitch, where she streamed games such as Bloodborne and The Walking Dead. She is also co-owner of 100 Thieves.

name: Zarbruh
about: Comedy video creator popular on TikTok where he is known as zarbruh. He has accrued more than 3.5 million fans on the platform.

name: Stephen Hawking
about: Legendary physicist who became renowned for creating a cosmology that relied on the unification of the theory of relativity and quantum mechanics. His 1988 book A Brief History of Time stayed on the British Sunday Times best-sellers list for a record-breaking 237 weeks.

name: David Bowie
about: Androgynous rock star of the 1960s and beyond who reinvented popular music with singles such as "Space Oddity" and "Starman." His first two albums to go platinum were 1971's Hunky Dory and 1972's The Rise and Fall of Ziggy Stardust and the Spiders from Mars.

name: Damiano David
about: Italian rock singer who rose to fame as the lead singer of the band Måneskin. He and the band competed on the popular talent show program The X Factor in 2017, which led to him amassing a following on his ykaaar Instagram account. The group also won the Eurovision Song Contest in 2021.

name: Adamkindacool
about: Content creator named Adam Dillon who is best known for his situational comedy sketches on TikTok, where he has over 3.1 million fans on his Adamkindacool account. He is also popular on Instagram with over 210,000 followers on his adamdillonn account.

name: Ryan Destiny
about: Urban pop singer and actress who became known as one third of the girl group Love Dollhouse. The group first gained fame following the release of their debut single "Can I." She is also recognizable for starring as April Geddes in the AMC series Low Winter Sun and as Alex in the FOX musical drama Star.

name: Rey Misterio Sr.
about: One of Mexico's top wrestlers and promoters in the 1970s and '80s, he was known for his signature move, the plancha, as well as his powerbomb finishing move.

name: Kim Jong-un
about: Son of Kim Jong-il who became the Supreme Leader of North Korea on December 17, 2011 at 29 years old, making him the world's youngest head of state. Due to North Korea's secretive policies, not much is known about his past or his rule.

name: Hooverr
about: YouTube star who has risen to fame for his Hooverr channel. He has risen to massive popularity for his commentary of fellow social media stars and cursed commercials after his inaugural video "Ugandan Knuckles | Wildlife Documentary" went viral in January 2018.

name: R. Kelly
about: Referred to as the King of R&B, he gained fame for such hits as "I Believe I Can Fly" and "Ignition (Remix)." With over 100 million records sold worldwide, he is one of the top-selling artists of all-time.

name: Kaash Paige
about: American R&B singer who is best known for her hit song "Love Songs." She has appeared on top playlists for both Apple Music and Spotify. She released her debut album titled Teenage Fever in August 2020.

name: Gia Giudice
about: Part of the all-girl music trio 3KT who is joined by her friends Alexa Maetta and Cristianna Cardinale. They released the music video for a cover of Britney Spears' "Circus" in 2014.

name: Joshua Perez
about: Lip syncing star who became popular through his thejoshuaperez account on the app musical.ly, which later became TikTok. He has more than 160,000 TikTok fans. He has set videos to the tune of songs by Nicki Minaj, John Legend, Drake, and countless other artists.

name: Isabella Durham
about: Younger sister of web star and actress Carrington Durham who gained a following on Instagram as well with over 150,000 followers. Like her sister, she has also acted and modeled. In 2017, she began appearing on the web series Chicken Girls.

name: Emilee Hembrow
about: Picture blogger on Instagram whose journey through pregnancy is shared on her self-titled account, which has earned over 1.2 million followers. She is also a part-time model and paid commercial worker.

name: Genevieve Padalecki
about: Actress who played Kris Furillo on the ABC Family drama Wildfire and played Ruby on Supernatural.

name: Emma Heesters
about: YouTube musician who is known for her Emma Heesters channel. She is particularly known for her frequent videos of her covering popular songs. She is also a singer and songwriter in her own right, and has been featured on various singles released to iTunes.

name: Isabel Bedoya
about: Self-taught beauty, fashion and wellness influencer on and offline whose exceeded 3.3 million followers on her itsisabelbedoya Instagram account. She has garnered over 430,000 YouTube subscribers as well.

name: Elleriemarie
about: Social media star who is best known for her elleriemarie TikTok account where she posts dance and vlog style videos. She has gained over 650,000 followers on the app.

name: Chris DiStefano
about: Known across social media as ItsDiStefano, he was an Instagram personality known for his collaborations with Lance Stewart.

name: Orkun Isitmak
about: Well known for his channel ThePersica, he is a popular YouTuber who has accumulated more than 9 million subscribers.

name: Kevin Parry
about: Stop-motion animator hired by the company Laika, where he worked on the major motion pictures The Boxtrolls and Kubo and the Two Strings. Animation videos and behind-the-scenes moments from his life as an animator have earned him more than 1.1 million followers on Instagram.

name: Rian McCririck
about: Television actor who rose to fame after being cast as Logan Bruno on The Baby-Sitters Club. This exposure has helped him to build a following on social media.

name: Cynthia Erivo
about: Drama Desk Award-winning and Tony Award-nominated theatre actress for her work in the Broadway production of The Color Purple who is also well known for her performance in the UK tour of Sister Act.

name: Jan Barba
about: Popular TikTok star who is best recognized for his jan_barba TikTok account where he posts comedy videos and skits. He has accumulated over 230,000 followers on the app. He has a following of over 10,000 on his jan_barba Instagram account where he has mainly shares selfies.

name: Queen Buenrostro
about: Instagram star and social media influencer who is known for posting both modeling pictures as well as lifestyle content to her over 7 million followers. She collaborated on content with the YouTube channel Badabun from 2018 to late 2019.

name: Tom Abisgold
about: English singer and theatre actor who became known in 2019 when his band Chapter 13 competed in Britain's Got Talent and received the Golden Buzzer.

name: David Silva
about: Midfielder who who joined the Spanish national team in 2006 and Manchester City in 2010. He helped lead Spain to its first-ever World Cup Championship in 2010.

name: Nanuka Gudavadze
about: Popular social media star and content creator who is best recognized for the bera_nanuka TikTok account she shares with her husband. They have earned over 6 million followers for their comedy and transition videos.

name: Khylin Rhambo
about: Known for his feature film debut as Dink Meeker in Ender's Game, he previously landed the starring role of Charles Johnson on BET Centric's The First Family. He later booked a recurring role on Teen Wolf.

name: Jennie Sofie
about: Beauty blogger, YouTuber, and Instagram star with more than 270,000 followers on the photo sharing app. She's become incredibly popular for her makeup tutorials, style tips, and food recommendations.

name: Zahara Jolie-Pitt
about: Daughter of Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt who has traveled the world with her celebrity parents.

name: Freddie Stroma
about: Played the role of Cormac McLaggen in Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince. His roles in Pitch Perfect, After the Dark and The Visitors bolstered his fame.

name: Ryan Sitkowski
about: Lead guitarist for the American metalcore group Motionless In White who replaced former guitarist Michael Costanza.

name: Ellis Records
about: British YouTuber whose daily life vlogs have amassed his channel 10,000 subscribers and 7,000 overall views. His real name is Ellis John Bainbridge. He is a professional videographer and photographer and advertises his work on his ellisrecords Instagram account.

name: Kate Quinlivan
about: Trending lip-sync performer who rose to fame by sharing a variety of videos on her katequinlivan TikTok account. Her videos have generated more than 12 million likes on the platform.

name: Shirley Bassey
about: Jazz singer who is known for her work on the theme songs for the James Bond movies Goldfinger, Diamonds are Forever, and Moonraker.

name: William Hartnell
about: English actor who played the original role of The Doctor on Doctor Who. He held the role from 1963 until 1966.

name: India Good
about: Social media star best known for her indiagood TikTok account where she posts lip-sync videos. She has gained over 550,000 followers on the app.

name: Rachel Cook
about: Popular content creator and model best known for the lifestyle, fashion and vlog-style videos she posts to her self-titled YouTube channel. Her videos have earned her over 180,000 subscribers on the platform. In November 2021 she began a detox challenge for mental health awareness.

name: Jenny Lewis
about: Indie rock singer and songwriter who released her first solo album, Rabbit Fur Coat, in 2006. She served as the lead singer of the band Rilo Kiley from 1998 to 2011 and began touring with her boyfriend Johnathan Rice as Jenny & Johnny in 2010.

name: Carolina Herrera
about: Venezuelan fashion designer and entrepreneur who founded her self-titled label in 1980. She has dressed celebrities such as Michelle Obama and Jacqueline Onassis.

name: Windell Middlebrooks
about: Nationally recognized for portraying the delivery man in Miller High Life beer commercials, he also played the character Kirby Morris on The Suite Life on Deck.

name: Allison Harvard
about: Wide-eyed model who is best known for finishing second on Cycle 12 of America's Next Top Model and America's Next Top Model: All-Stars.

name: Retta
about: Lifestyle and beauty social media influencer popular on Instagram who has earned more than 550,000 followers. Her account is called retta.a.

name: Brent Rivera
about: Social media star across multiple platforms who is best known for his self-titled YouTube, which was formerly MrBrent98. His YouTube channel has earned over 17 million subscribers. He was also extremely popular on Vine, where he earned over 8 million followers. In 2019, he began hosting the web series Dream Vacation. He co-founded the digital content group Amp Studios and he has served as the CEO of the brand.

name: Blake Gray
about: Social star who became part of the Impact MeetandGreet.Me touring group and who also appeared on DigiTour Slaybells 2015. He has earned over 10 million TikTok followers and more than 5 million followers on Instagram. The majority of his TikToks feature short dance routines and many of them include friends of his. He was a member of the Magcon 2016 tour.

name: Nina Dobrev
about: Became known to television audiences for her Teen Choice Award-winning role as Elena Gilbert/Katherine Pierce on The Vampire Diaries. Her film credits include The Perks of Being a Wallflower and The Roommate.

name: Wengie
about: Australian-Chinese beauty and lifestyle YouTube sensation who runs one of Australia's top blogs, The Wonderful World of Wengie. She also has a self-titled YouTube channel that has more than 13 million subscribers. On the channel, she is known for testing TikTok life hacks and for posting slime content.

name: Liana Jade Brooker
about: Welsh TikTok star whose singing, dancing and fitness videos have amassed her 6 million fans. She has uploaded multiple videos cutting from her natural face to her face wearing elaborate makeup.

name: Damaury Mikula
about: Popular social media star who posts comedy and lip-sync videos on his damaurymikula TikTok account. His videos have earned him over 4.2 million followers on the app.

name: Deshae Frost
about: Stand-up comedian who earned a following on Instagram with his comedy videos. He played Darryl Henderson on CBS's SWAT from 2017 until 2018. He has opened for the likes of comedians such as Faizon Love and Tiffany Haddish.

name: Kate Middleton
about: Officially known as Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge. She married Prince William, Duke of Cambridge, in April 2011 after dating him for nine years. She is the daughter-in-law of the late Princess Diana.

name: Toosii
about: Rapper also known as KingToosii who rose to fame on SoundCloud. His 2017 album Label Me Diverse was released to Spinrilla. He first gained an audience for singles like "Lost" and "Dreams."

name: Eret
about: Streamer and content creator who is best known for their Eret Twitch channel where they post Minecraft gaming videos. They have gained over 1.1 million subscribers on the platform. Their popular instagram account has often featured photos of themselves and their friends and they have over 1 million followers.

name: Sean Paul
about: Jamaican singer who has collaborated with a number of artists, including Beyonce, Akon, Snoop Dogg and Rihanna. His 2002 album Dutty Rock reached number 1 on the US Rap Billboard charts and went RIAA double platinum.

name: Flo Milli
about: Notable for her raw and honest vocals, she is a rap artist who returned to the limelight with the single "Beef FloMix" in early 2019 after dropping the song "Not Friendly" ten months prior.

name: Elijah Daniel
about: Actor and writer best known for being an internet personality on Twitter and YouTube. He has been featured in several movies, TV shows, and commercials and was also featured in the music video "BADMAN" by the Korean rap group B.A.P. In 2019, he began appearing on the reality series The Reality House, which features various YouTubers.

name: Tommy the Clown
about: Dancer who is best known as the inventor of the dance style "clowning," which evolved into the better-known krumping. He created the style in 1992, which thereby created the "hip-hop clown."

name: Nicola Peltz
about: Child actress who played Katara in the 2010 fantasy film The Last Airbender and appeared in the Twilight saga. She played Bradley Martin in the television series Bates Motel and Tessa in Transformers: Age of Extinction.

name: Emily Mariko
about: Social star best known for posting cooking videos to her popular TikTok account, which has earned over 7 million fans. She first built a social following by posting style videos, hauls and skincare routines on her self-titled YouTube channel.

name: Jackson Mecham
about: Famous for his appearances in his parents' popular YouTube videos, he has helped the Ellie and Jared channel reach over 1.6 million subscribers. He has also gained over 20,000 followers on his parent-run Instagram page.

name: Nicole García
about: Social media star who first rose to fame through her self-titled YouTube channel, where she has earned over 1 million subscribers. She then went on to earn over 9 million fans on TikTok, where she posts comedy and dance videos, often featuring friends. She was part of the popular YouTube channel Dosogas. She has been represented by Influencia Talent.

name: Jailyne Ojeda Ochoa
about: Fitness model who has gained a large following on social media, attracting more than 13 million followers to her Instagram account. She has done promotion work for various night clubs in Arizona and has appeared in several commercials and music videos. She has also been a brand ambassador for the Fashion Nova company.

name: Anais Lee
about: Actress best known for her childhood acting debut in the 2013 film Blood Ties. In 2020, she appeared as the character Jessi Ramsey on the Netflix series The Baby-Sitters Club (2020).

name: Domo Glo Twins
about: Content creator who, along with her sister Danny, became best known for their Glo Twins YouTube channel. Their original vlogs, pranks and challenges have been viewed a combined 11 million times.

name: Richard Nixon
about: The 37th President of the United States who became the first US president to resign from office, relinquishing the position in the aftermath of the 1974 Watergate Scandal.

name: Jimmy Page
about: Best known as a Led Zeppelin guitarist and songwriter who Rolling Stone Magazine ranked third on their list of The 100 Greatest Guitarists of All Time. He co-wrote the classic rock staple "Stairway to Heaven" with Led Zeppelin singer Robert Plant, and the song features one of his most impressive guitar solos.

name: Holygxd
about: Social media star who is widely known for his Holygxd Instagram account. He has gained popularity there for his personal photos and comedic vignettes with friends.

name: Jace Williams
about: Collegiate softball star who signed with Otto Models in 2014. She participated in the Women's College World Series in both 2011 (5th place finish) and 2012 (3rd place finish) with the University of California at Berkeley.

name: Cody Carson
about: Lead vocalist of the punk/symphonic rock band Set It Off who initially helped the band gain a following through his YouTube channel rockmaniac89. The band's first EP was titled Baby, You Don't Tripajaharda.

name: Avery Christine
about: YouTube star who was best known as a Monday vlogger for the SevenPerfectAngels channel, a sub channel of the SevenAwesomeKids network. The SevenPerfectAngels channel earned upwards of 3 million subscribers.

name: Lauryn McClain
about: Singer and actress who gained fame for her childhood film role in Daddy's Little Girls. She also starred in Step Up: High Water as Janelle Baker.

name: James Acaster
about: Comedian whose 2012 act "Prompt" was nominated for an Edinburgh Comedy Award. He also received a New Zealand Comedy Guild honor in 2013.

name: J.K. Simmons
about: Received an Academy Award and a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role in the 2014 film Whiplash. He also plays Jonah Jameson, editor in chief of the Daily Bugle, in the Tobey Maguire Spider-Man trilogy. His other notable films include Thank You for Smoking, The Jackal, and Juno.

name: Dayana's Life
about: Social media star who has gained fame for her Dayana's Life YouTube channel. She has risen to massive popularity for her fashion and beauty tips and tutorials alongside school hauls and adventure vlogs.

name: Chad Johnson
about: NFL wide receiver formerly known as Chad Ochocinco. He was a 6-time Pro Bowl selection and 3-time All-Pro during his ten seasons with the Cincinnati Bengals.

name: Julie Chrisley
about: Matriarch of the Chrisley family known for starring on the reality series Chrisley Knows Best.

name: LØREN
about: Pop singer-songwriter who is recognized for the single "Empty Trash." The single's accompanying music video has been viewed more than 4 million times on YouTube.

name: Max Balegde
about: Short-form content creator who is best recognized for the random lists he posts to his max_balegde TikTok account. He has accumulated over 1.5 million followers on the social media platform.

name: Joshua Weissman
