name: Savannah Liles
about: Actress who is famous for her roles throughout film and TV, including on American Horror Story and OMG! She rose to widespread prominence in 2017 for starring in the thriller film Prodigy as Ellie.

name: Mikayla Poe
about: Point-of-view style content creator best known for sharing lip sync performances on her mikaypjadee TikTok account. She has built a fan base of more than 1.5 million followers on the platform.

name: Lawrence Taylor
about: New York Giants linebacker known as "LT" who is considered by many to be the greatest linebacker ever. He was a 2-time Super Bowl Champion, 10-time Pro Bowl selection, and the 1986 NFL Most Valuable Player. He retired with 132.5 career sacks and 1,088 tackles.

name: Oscar de la Hoya
about: Legendary boxer known as "The Golden Boy," he compiled a record of 39-6 and won a gold medal at the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona, competing in the lightweight class. He defeated 17 world champions over the course of his career.

name: Natalie Krill
about: Perhaps most well known for her recurring role in season 2 of The Next Step, she is a dancer and actress who played Molly McBride in the hockey drama MVP.

name: Riccardo Marcuzzo
about: Singer under the stage name of Riccardo, he is a pop singer with singles titled "Sei Mia" and "Diverso." He was a reality show competitor on the series Amici. In 2018, he released a song featuring CNCO titled "Dolor de Cabeza."

name: Kimberly Wyatt
about: Former member of The Pussycat Dolls who formed a new group, called Her Majesty & the Wolves, in 2010. She has also pursued a solo career, releasing singles like "Derriere." In 2019, she began starring as Sasha on Almost Never.

name: Jonathan Carlin
about: YouTube vlogger known for being part of the brother duo channel SuperCarlinBrothers. The channel is known for a variety of videos from vlogs to movie facts.

name: Gavin DeGraw
about: Singer-songwriter best known for recording the One Tree Hill theme song, "I Don't Want to Be." He also released singles like "Chariot" and "Not Over You."

name: Aizat Nazri
about: Also known as Jiggy, he is a comedian and actor who has been a television and radio personality. His jiggymasin Instagram account has earned more than 260,000 followers.

name: Bonnie Builds
about: YouTube content creator and gaming personality who rose to fame by publishing Roblox speed builds and roleplays. She has more than 250,000 subscribers on the platform.

name: Cristiano Ronaldo
about: One of the top soccer players in the world, he rose to fame as a forward for Real Madrid after being acquired from Manchester United for a $131.6 million transfer fee in 2009. He became captain of the Portuguese national team in 2008 and received the Ballon d'Or in 2008, 2013, 2014, 2016 and 2017. In 2018, he signed with Juventus. He was signed to return to Manchester United in 2021.

name: Neymar
about: Superstar forward who starred for Santos from 2009 to 2013 and FC Barcelona from 2013 to 2017. His transfer to Paris Saint-Germain FC in 2017 cost €222 million, the most expensive transfer in history. He debuted with the Brazilian national team in 2010 and became the team's second-highest goalscorer of all-time.

name: Nick Crompton
about: Entrepreneur who first gained popularity on YouTube, then became a co-founder of the social media marketing agency Social Chain. He also became the COO of the popular web group Team 10 up until his departure in 2018. He's widely known for his song "England Is My City" featuring Jake Paul and Team 10.

name: Kevin Perry
about: Comedy personality on TikTok who has earned more than 2.8 million fans on his Kevboyperry account. On December 29, 2018, he dropped a single called "Maybe You Don't Understand" under the artist name Kevin Creel.

name: Kevin Gates
about: Louisiana-based rapper who broke onto the rap scene with the 2013 mixtape The Luca Brasi Story. He signed to Atlantic Records in the winter of 2013.

name: Nils Kuesel
about: Lip-sync content creator and social media personality who rose to fame on nilskue account. He has over 4.9 million followers on TikTok.

name: Bobby Brown
about: R&B singer who founded New Edition, the group known for songs such as "Cool It Now" and "Mr. Telephone Man." As a solo artist, he released the hit song "My Prerogative."

name: Darren Criss
about: Became known to television audiences as Blaine Anderson on Fox's Glee. He won a Broadway World Award in 2011 for his role in Starship. In 2019, he won the Golden Globe for Best Actor in a Limited Series or TV Movie for his portrayal of serial killer Andrew Cunanan in The Assassination of Gianni Versace: American Crime Story.

name: Davis Cleveland
about: Actor and rapper who won over audiences as Flynn Jones on Disney's Shake It Up, receiving nominations for Young Artist Awards in both 2011 and 2012.

name: Jisung
about: Member of the unit NCT Dream that is part of the S.M. Entertainment-formed South Korean boy group NCT. He has appeared in the variety shows Exo 90:2014 and Mickey Mouse Club, and the reality shows NCT Life in Bangkok and NCT Life: Entertainment Retreat. His full name is Park Jisung.

name: Jeremy Sumpter
about: At 14, he starred as Peter Pan in the 2003 live-action film version of the classic tale. Later, he starred alongside Helen Hunt in Soul Surfer.

name: C.cessarr
about: Interactive comedy content creator who is recognized for posting short videos on his self titled TikTok account. His point-of-view style videos have garnered him a fanbase of more than 1.5 million followers. He has posted multiple POV videos where he acts like he is playing the spin the bottle game.

name: Flossie Clegg
about: YouTube star who is famous for her Flossie channel. She has garnered massive popularity there for her makeup routines and tutorials, as well as lifestyle vlogs and routines. She posted a video of herself doing the unhealthy Victoria's Secret diet and received over 2.4 million views on the video.

name: Taehyun
about: South Korean singer also known as Kang Tae Hyun who was announced as a member of TXT, the second boy's band to be released by Big Hit Entertainment since BTS.

name: Christen Dominique
about: YouTube beauty phenomenon and freelance makeup artist whose online fame extends to her Instagram account, where she has over 1.6 million followers. She has also created her own successful cruelty-free Dominique Cosmetics beauty company.

name: Steven Suptic
about: Minecraft gaming commentator and animator known as mlgHwnT who joined ZexyZek, MigMacNation, and others the collaborative channel, Team MVG. He later created the Sugar Pine 7 channel, which went on to amass over 1 million subscribers.

name: Trayvon Martin
about: 17-year-old American high school student who, while walking home from a convenience store, was shot and killed by American neighborhood watch coordinator George Zimmerman in a gated community in Sanford, Florida. Zimmerman claimed self defense and was acquitted of his second-degree murder and manslaughter charges on July 13, 2013.

name: Hannah Herrmann
about: YouTuber known for her self-titled channel which was previously called Miss Hannah Beauty. She covers topics including beauty, fashion, lifestyle, and creates DIY videos.

name: Matt Watson
about: Became known for his posts to his channel called Kids w/ Problems, which has earned over 120,000 subscribers. He has a secondary channel called SuperMega and also became a member of the group Game Grumps.

name: Henry Golding
about: Television personality, actor and model who is most famous for being the star reality shows Surviving Borneo and Welcome To The Railworld Japan. After appearing on those shows, he began being cast in feature films like Crazy Rich Asians and A Simple Favor.

name: Peter Kang
about: Short form comedy content creator who rose to fame by posting videos on his peterkang0 TikTok account. His popularity on the platform led to him amassing more than 3 million followers.

name: Tiwa Savage
about: Nigerian R&B singer who released her debut single, "Without My Heart," in 2011. She has cowritten songs for other artists, like Fantasia Barrino's "Collard Greens & Cornbread."

name: Hank Aaron
about: Legendary right fielder known as the Hammer who set an MLB record with 755 career home runs, breaking Babe Ruth's record of 714 in 1974. He was a 25-time All-Star, 4-time National League home run champion, 2-time National League batting champion, and 1-time National League MVP over the course of his 23-year career, which was spent with the Milwaukee and Atlanta Braves and the Milwaukee Brewers.

name: SnaggyMo
about: YouTube star who has gained fame for his SnaggyMo channel. His public interviews, pranks and challenges have helped him garner huge popularity.

name: Andy Cowley
about: YouTuber and voice actor who is known for his gaming channel TheDragonHat. He is also known for his voice acting work for various video games and online animation series and films.

name: The Camping Rusher
about: Born Brayden Wheeler, he is famous for his Minecraft Let's Play videos. His YouTube channel has attracted over 1.6 million subscribers and he also has more than 160,000 followers on Twitter.

name: Michael Sheen
about: Known for his roles as Tony Blair in The Queen and David Frost in Frost/Nixon. He also appeared in the 1992 stage adaptation of Romeo and Juliet and played a role in the 2010 film, The Special Relationship. In 2013, he began playing Dr. William Masters on the Showtime series Masters of Sex.

name: Alex Brightman
about: Broadway star who landed the lead role in School of Rock the Musical at the Winter Garden Theatre after previously performing in Broadway productions of Big Fish and Beetlejuice.

name: Jennifer Michele
about: Television actress who rose to fame for her performances on 9-1-1, Manny's Garage Sale: A Hitchcock Knot, and Matty Paz Is a Noob. She was cast as the lead in the family film Joey and Ella.

name: Joseph Cuaton
about: TikTok star and influencer who is best recognized for sharing viral dance videos through his account for his over 5 million fans. He is also known for his lip synch videos and his utilization of unique transitions which have helped him earn over 92 million total likes on his videos.

name: Moonfallx
about: Roblox player who is known online for her YouTube channel Moonfallx, which is dedicated almost entirely to the MMO. She has won more than 150,000 subscribers with original Roblox series as "Remember Me" as well as Roblox short films like "Broken."

name: Adassa
about: American reggaeton artist who has come to be referred to in the media as "Reggaetón Princess." She has found popularity as a solo artist with singles like "De Tra" as well as a featured artist on songs by artists like Missy Elliott and Ciara.

name: Jess No Limit
about: Mobile Legends gamer who achieved the status of no. 1 globally in the game for season 6. The gameplay on his YouTube channel earned him more than 23 million subscribers.

name: Juan Karlos Labajo
about: Second runner-up on the 1st season of ABS-CBN's Filipino version of the reality singing competition series The Voice Kids. Following his successful run, he was signed by Star Magic.

name: Chamar Moore
about: American content creator and social media celebrity who found fame after launching her self-titled YouTube channel. She posts a combination of vlogs, story times, routines and beauty tutorials for over 240,000 subscribers.

name: Hunter Dillon
about: Television actor best recognized for his role as Tyler Flaherty on the Hulu series Holly Hobbie. He is also known for having starred in recurring roles on both The Exorcist series and Beyblade Burst.

name: Duff McKagan
about: Rock bassist best known for his time with Guns N' Roses and Velvet Revolver. He has also served as an occasional writer for SeattleWeekly.com.

name: Luke Newton
about: British actor and singer who became best known for starring on Disney Channel UK's The Lodge as Ben Evans. He'd previously been featured on The Cut as Luke Atwood.

name: Sidney Starr
about: Transgender internet sensation renowned for her videos posted to World Star Hip Hop. She has become and Instagram superstar, earning more than 340,000 dedicated fans. She also became a cast member of Love & Hip Hop: New York.

name: Catherine De Mayo
about: Creator of squishy toy content whose videos on the YouTube channel CathyDM have earned her more than 200,000 subscribers.

name: Jeremy Beau
about: Scooter rider who was a member of the BeauBros YouTube channel with his brother. Along with scooter videos, they uploaded videos of themselves doing bottle flips on trampolines. He competed at the 2016 ISA World Championship in Barcelona.

name: Ayanna Sabrina
about: Short-form content creator who is best known for her ayannasabrina TikTok account where she posts makeup tutorials and anonymous storytimes from her followers. She has accumulated over 2.5 million followers on the social media platform.

name: Alison Hammond
about: British television presenter who became well known for appearing on the third series of Big Brother (UK) in 2002. She has since appeared on many reality TV programs such as Celebrity Fit Club and I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here.

name: Sara Evans
about: American country singer who has released gold and platinum-selling records, including her 1998 album No Place That Far.

name: Carlos Tévez
about: Argentinian forward who joined Juventus in 2013 and was a member of Argentina's national team from 2004 to 2011.

name: Stina Talling
about: YouTube star who is widely known for her self-titled YouTube channel's content. She has gained popularity there for her fashion, DIY, lifestyle, and friend tag vlogs.

name: Auden Barnes
about: Entertainer on TikTok who is notable for his comedy, lip-sync and other types of videos. He has earned more than 490,000 followers for his account unclebenmybrudda. He has often featured his grandmother in his comedic skits.

name: Chris Trott
about: Well known as Trottimus, he represents the T in HAT Films and is a member of the Yogscast family. He is joined by his partners Ross Hornby and Alex Smith as the gamers behind Hat Films.

name: Bob Marley
about: Born Nesta Robert Marley, he became known as the Ambassador of Third World for his music and sold over 75 million reggae albums worldwide. He died of cancer at Cedars of Lebanon Hospital in Miami, Florida.

name: Rick Astley
about: Pop singer whose 1987 single "Never Gonna Give You Up" reached #1 in more than twenty countries. He won Best Act Ever at the 2008 MTV Europe Music Awards.

name: Charlie Heaton
about: Rising actor who became best known for his portrayal of Jonathan Byers in the Netflix hit series Stranger Things. He starred in the 2016 horror film Shut In and has other film credits in As You Are and Urban & the Shed Crew. In 2020, he played Cannonball in the movie The New Mutants.

name: Babe Ruth
about: Revered by many as the greatest baseball player of all time, he set career records for home runs, RBIs, and bases on balls that have since been broken. He won 7 World Series Championships, 12 American League home run titles, 6 AL RBI titles and the 1924 AL batting title. He played for the New York Yankees from 1920 to 1934 after the Boston Red Sox traded him in exchange for cash.

name: Joe Bartolozzi
about: Relatable TikTok personality and comedy content creator known for his verified joe.bartolozzi account. He has built a fanbase of more than 16 million followers on the platform.

name: Ronald Reagan
about: 40th president of the United States whose controversial economics philosophy, Reaganomics, impacted the latter part of the 20th century.

name: Crystal Reed
about: American television and film actress who became known to audiences for her roles in the 2011 film Crazy, Stupid, Love and MTV's Teen Wolf. In 2019, she began starring in DC Universe's Swamp Thing.

name: JR Stuber
about: Selfie and self-portrait taking Instagram personality who has attracted more than 170,000 followers to his self-titled account. He has also come out with a hoodie line called "CONTENT".

name: Tinashe
about: Versatile talent known simply as Tinashe who has released the acclaimed mixtapes In Case We Die and Reverie. Her 2014 single "2 On" featuring Schoolboy Q peaked at #21 on the US R&B chart.

name: Dominic Sherwood
about: Best known for his role as Christian Ozera in the 2014 film Vampire Academy, he also starred on the television series Shadowhunters. He appeared in the films Charlie and the Chocolate Factory and Stormbreaker.

name: Dane DeHaan
about: Played the lead role of Andrew in the science fiction film Chronicle and has also played prominent roles in such films as Lawless, Kill Your Darlings, and The Place Beyond the Pines. He also portrayed Jesse D'Amato on HBO's In Treatment.

name: Axl Rose
about: Known for his high-pitched vocals and overall vocal range, he became famous as the animated lead singer of Guns N' Roses. The band's best known songs include "Welcome to the Jungle," "Paradise City," and "Sweet Child o' Mine."

name: Rickey Thompson
about: YouTube star with more than 1.2 million subscribers, he first became popular on Vine, where he finished with more than 2 million followers. He landed a starring role in an AwesomenessTV web series titled Foursome in 2016. He also became host of his own Snapchat show Trend or End.

name: Bianca Heinicke
about: Fashion, beauty, and lifestyle video blogger who would become the most successful German female YouTuber in 2014. Her channel has more than 5 million subscribers. She also runs the musical.ly account Bibi & Julian with her partner Julienco.

name: Shelby Simmons
about: One of the stars of the feature film Selfie Dad, she previously became notable for her recurring part in the hit Disney series Andi Mack. In 2018, she'd begin starring as Sydney Quinn in Netflix's Prince of Peoria and in 2019, she began starring as Ava on Bunk'd.

name: Jada Williams
about: Point guard who plays for Blue Springs High School. Her Amateur Athletic Union team it  the Missouri Phenom. By the time the age of 13, she had already received Division I scholarship offers from Illinois and Syracuse, and had received interest from over a dozen colleges.

name: Samantha Partida
about: TikTok star who rose to fame posting popular lip sync videos to the platform. She has over 500,000 followers. She posted a video about her unique drink cover for staying safe at nightclubs and the video has been seen over 5.4 million times.

name: Kaylina Eileen Garcia
about: Instagram star who has earned more than 360,000 followers through her selfies and dance videos. She has posted numerous outfit and bikini photos on her page. She has also had a paid partnership with the Boom Bod weight loss drink company.

name: Aaron Burr
about: Third Vice President of the United States from 1801 to 1805 who was one of the first Senators from New York. He infamously killed his rival, Alexander Hamilton, in a duel.

name: Ariel Mortman
about: Best known to American audiences as Hayley Woods in the Netflix original series Greenhouse Academy. She previously starred in Disney's Northern Star from 2014 to 2016, which ran in Israel.

name: Reed Deming
about: Pop artist who reached the Top 24 on the 2012 season of The X Factor. A multi-instrumentalist, he plays the guitar, bass, alto sax, tenor sax and keyboards.

name: Allison Holker
about: American dancer best known for appearing on season two of So You Think You Can Dance. She went on to become a So You Think You Can Dance all-star. She also appears as a dancer on the VH1 drama Hit the Floor.

name: Bradlee Wannemacher
about: Popular YouTube content creator as well as recording artist who rose to fame in 2013 when he was a contestant on The X Factor. He then became a contestant on American Idol season 14, where he placed in the top 38 best auditions during Boot Camp week.

name: Ryan Swaze
about: Comedic personality on YouTube who has earned more than 800,000 subscribers through his seemingly random assortment of videos.

name: Rachel Marie
about: Level 7 gymnast who landed the Saturday spot on the hugely popular SevenGymnasticsGirls channel. She created a self-titled channel in August of 2014 to post mainly about gymnastics and acrobatics.

name: Kris Humphries
about: NBA forward who joined the league in 2004 with the Utah Jazz before moving to the New Jersey/Brooklyn Nets and Boston Celtics.

name: Sahar Dahi
about: Point-of-view content creator who rose to fame by sharing lip sync and story time videos on her saharrooo account. Her videos have received more than 120 million likes on the platform.

name: Bryniebooo
about: Popular TikTok star who gained popularity for the hairstyle videos she posts to her bryniebooo TikTok account. Her lifestyle and vlog videos have earned her over 1.6 million followers on the platform.

name: Nora Fatehi
about: Canadian-Moroccan actress known for her roles in Bollywood films, notably Crazy Cukkad Family, Mr. X, and Kick 2. She released her first English song "Pepeta" with Rayvanny in 2019.

name: Aviva Mongillo
about: Canadian actress and singer known for her role on Backstage as Alya Kendrick. She was also cast in the 2017 film Don't Talk to Irene.

name: Dalton Rapattoni
about: Guitarist and singer who performed with the pop boy band IM5 before rejoining Fly Away Hero as a singer. He finished in third place on American Idol season 15 in 2016.

name: Katherine Elizabeth
about: Gamer who has risen to fame for her Katherine Elizabeth Gaming YouTube channel. Her Minecraft tutorials, tips, and Let's Plays have helped her amass more than 800,000 subscribers.

name: Kierra Luv
about: Social media star and rapper who is famous for her rxcan Instagram account. She has gained massive popularity for her original rap cyphers and selfies.

name: Alex Drachnik
about: Short form comedy content creator on TikTok who is recognized for her popular "American vs. Russian" skit series. She has more than 1.8 million fans on her drachnik account. She shares comedic content on her self named YouTube channel, where she has gained 90,000 subscribers.

name: Swagatronforever
about: TikTok content creator and social media personality known for posting comedic outfit of the day videos and storytime content. She has amassed more than 4.8 million followers on the platform.

name: Brian Stepanek
about: Comedic actor who has had roles on the shows Kick Buttowski: Suburban Daredevil and The Suite Life of Zack & Cody. In 2014, he began appearing on Nickelodeon's Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn.

name: Zircon
about: YouTube sensation who went viral with his video "Logan Paul (My Hero) - An Original Song by Zircon." He went on to create a collaborative channel known as Flobros, which now has over 440,000 subscribers.

name: Snifferish
about: Twitch star and gamer who has gained popularity for her snifferish Twitch channel where she posts Minecraft content. She has accumulated over 550,000 subscribers on the streaming platform.

name: Hannah Pettit
about: Adopted daughter and member of the Crazy Pieces family vlog. Her parents Aaron and Crystal adopted her and share several more adopted and biological children.

name: Dylan Efron
about: Younger brother of former Disney star turned movie star Zac Efron. He has over 750,000 followers on Instagram. He is an outdoor enthusiast, with fly fishing being one of his favorite hobbies.

name: Eva Braun
about: Also known as Eva Hitler, she was the companion and brief wife of Nazi dictator Adolf Hitler. They were married for less than 40 hours.

name: Karl Kugelmann
about: South African social star who is best known for posting transition videos to his karl_kugelmann TikTok account, which has earned over 6 million fans. He is also known for his modeling, lifestyle, and travel photos on Instagram. He has worked professionally as a model.

name: Gemma Forsyth
about: Actress, dancer and model who is most well known for her role as Evie McLaren in the hit series Mako Mermaids.

name: Kyilee Ann Elsten
about: TikTok personality who has gained fame for her self-titled channel. Her lip-syncing to popular music and dubbing have helped her amass a sizable following.

name: Zsa Zsa Gabor
about: Hungarian-born celebrity and actress who many came to know as the sister of Eva Gabor. Her credits include A Nightmare on Elm Street 3: Dream Warriors and The Naked Gun 2 1/2: The Smell of Fear.

name: Mackenzie Smith
about: American actress who played the child role of Savannah on the science fiction television series Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles.

name: ItsBsd
about: Comedy video creator on TikTok who incorporates music into his videos. His personality has attracted more than 12 million fans to his account.

name: Jade Jurgens
about: Social media starlet who has earned fame for her jadejurgenss TikTok channel. Her dances to popular music alongside lip-syncs have helped her garner a massive following.

name: Jacksepticeye
about: Energetic video game commentator who features content on games such as Five Nights at Freddy's, Grand Theft Auto and God of War on his jacksepticeye YouTube channel. The channel has earned over 27 million subscribers. He has also diversified his content, posting videos where he recaps life events, comments on TikToks and reacts to scary videos.

name: Gabbie Hanna
about: YouTube phenomenon whose self-titled channel has earned over 5 million subscribers. She is known for posting pranks, challenges, vlogs, story time videos, and rants. Also a singer and actress, she released her debut single "Out Loud" in 2017, and starred in the YouTube series Escape the Night.

name: Aaron Doh
about: Social media star who first became known for his over-the-top outbursts on Vine, where he earned more than 1 million followers. He later found success on TikTok where he has amassed over 7 million fans to his aarondoh account. In August 2018, he released his first album called Love Lies.

name: Remi Cruz
about: Beauty guru and video blogger known for her two YouTube channels, MissRemiAshten and RemLife. She has over 3 million subscribers between the two channels. She'd later star on the controversial podcast called Pretty Basic with Alisha Marie.

name: Ashton Kutcher
about: First gained recognition for his role as Michael Kelso on Fox's That '70s Show. His success on the series earned him leading roles in such films as Jobs, Spread, The Butterfly Effect, and Dude, Where's My Car?

name: Tae Caldwell
about: YouTube personality and broadcaster who rose to fame as a member of the popular challenge, prank, and story time channel Jazz and Tae alongside her former girlfriend Jazmine Hood. The channel has amassed more than 4 million subscribers. She has also gained over 400,000 followers on her tae_caldwell Instagram where she has posted multiple photos wearing the brand Fashion Nova.

name: Bea Miller
about: Pop artist who, as a teenager, sang many hit songs while competing on The X Factor, including Cyndi Lauper's "Time After Time."

name: Chris Rock
about: Comedian and actor who rose to prominence as a cast member on Saturday Night Live from 1990 to 1993. He's played starring roles in the films Down to Earth, I Think I Love My Wife, Dogma, Grown Ups and Top Five and he provided the voice for Marty the zebra in the Madagascar films.

name: LaToya Forever
about: Popular YouTube personality who frequently features Ask Latoya: Q&A, Outfit of the Day, topical, parody, and relationship videos on her self-titled channel. She also became a TV reality star on The Real Housewives of Atlanta.

name: Isaiah Thomas
about: Known as The Pizza Boy, he is a 5'9" point guard who began his NBA career with the Sacramento Kings in 2011. He went on to play for the Phoenix Suns, Boston Celtics, Cleveland Cavaliers and Los Angeles Lakers. He signed with the Denver Nuggets in 2018 and the following year joined the Washington Wizards.

name: Garth Brooks
about: Pop country singer and musician who was named the Best-Selling Solo Artist of the Century in the United States by the RIAA in 2007.

name: Charles Dickens
about: Renowned 19th-century English author whose best known works include Oliver Twist, Bleak House, and A Christmas Carol. He created some of the most memorable characters in fiction, became known for his acute social satire, and is generally considered to be the most significant novelist of the Victorian era.

name: Steve Nash
about: Legendary NBA point guard who won the MVP Award in 2005 and 2006 with the Phoenix Suns and played in eight NBA All-Star games. In 2020, he was named head coach of the Brooklyn Nets.

name: Cepillín
about: TV presenter, clown and singer who worked on the educational programming channel Televisa.

name: Jeremy Meeks
about: Gained attention for his model-esque looks after his leaked mugshot went viral in 2014. His viral mugshot earned over 60,000 "likes" on Facebook and was shown on major news outlets across the United States.

name: Pierre Gasly
about: French formula racing driver who is best known for being the 2016 GP2 Series champion. He drove a Honda-powered car for Team Mugen. He has been a member of the AlphaTauri team.

name: Ovie Soko
about: Professional basketball player and television personality who is recognized for having played the small forward position for UCAM Murcia of the Liga ACB. In 2019, he competed on the reality dating series Love Island.

name: Laura Ingalls Wilder
about: Author of the autobiographical American pioneer-themed Little House on the Prairie series. Her family's years in Wisconsin became the basis of two of the most popular books in the series: Little House on the Prairie and Little House in the Big Woods.

name: Matthew Stafford
about: NFL quarterback who was the #1 pick of the Detroit Lions in the 2009 NFL Draft. He quickly became the team's starting quarterback and helped lead the team to the playoffs in 2011, 2014 and 2016. He was traded to the Los Angeles Rams in 2021.

name: Cerina Vincent
about: Became known for her role as Areola, a foreign exchange student who appeared nude throughout the spoof film Not Another Teen Movie. In 2016, she began playing the role of Suzy Diaz on the Disney series Stuck in the Middle.

name: 420.justin
about: Primarily a comedic personality, he is a video creator on TikTok named Justin Diaz who has garnered more than 1.1 million fans to his 420.justin account. He surpassed both 200,000 fans and 5 million hearts on TikTok in June of 2019.

name: Desmond Doss
about: Combat medic of the United States Army during World War II who distinguished himself during the Battle of Okinawa. He saved 75 wounded infantrymen while refusing to kill an enemy soldier or carry a weapon into combat due to his Seventh-day Aventist beliefs.

name: BabyFace Ray
about: Team Eastside affiliated rapper notable for his collaborative effort with G.T. called Gt X Mia. He followed it up with a mixtape of his own called My Cup of Tea. His 2021 album Unf*ckwitable received a 6/10 rating from Pitchfork.

name: Lola Holderness
about: Daughter of communications mogul and YouTube sensation Penn Holderness. She and the rest of her family appear on the YouTube channel The Holderness Family.

name: Xenia Goodwin
about: Actress and dancer who starred as Tara Webster on the ABC TV show Dance Academy.

name: Marissa Dania
about: Daughter of Malaysian actor Mohamed Nurhakim Zaidon and actress Abby Abadi. She became extremely popular on Instagram, earning over 460,000 followers on her marissadania_ account.

name: FalcoPunch
about: German Tik Tok star whose lip-sync content has earned him 10 million fans and the verification crown.

name: gabschase
about: TikTok star best recognized for posting comedy videos, rants, storytimes and lifestyle videos to her gabschase account, which has earned over 2.7 million followers.

name: Jasmine Adams
about: Electro-pop singer and makeup artist known professionally as Jazmin Bean. They are best known for their WorldWide Torture EP, which was released in August of 2019. Their pastel goth glamour and kawaii aesthetic are showcased on their jazminbean Instagram account, which has attracted 600,000 fans.

name: Stephen Hilton
about: Composer who's worked on some of the biggest movies, including favorites such as Transformers: Dark of the Moon, the Oceans 11 movies, and Moulin Rouge.

name: James Spader
about: Gained prominence for his role in the 1989 film Sex, Lies, and Videotape. His roles in Pretty in Pink, Crash, Stargate, and Lincoln earned him additional fame. He also portrayed Alan Shore on Boston Legal and, in 2013, he began playing Raymond Reddington on the series The Blacklist.

name: Joseph Ansara
about: Dancer grown popular through the lip syncing app TikTok, he has earned more than 1.1 million fans by posting short dance clips to the music of Rihanna, Jason Derulo, and numerous others.

name: RJ Hampton
about: Point guard who in high school was ranked number 4 on the ESPN 25 in 2017. He joined the Orlando Magic in 2021. He was named Eastern Conference rookie of the month for the month of May 2021.

name: Jake Goldberg
about: Actor best known for playing the role of Greg Feder in Grown Ups and Grown Ups 2 alongside Adam Sandler. In 2010, he played Young Scarlip in Choose. He later took a hiatus from acting to attend school.

name: Marlo Hampton
about: Fashion guru personality from The Real Housewives of Atlanta, and also seen in the reality series I Dream of NeNe, who has previously worked as a private stylist in addition to being an entrepreneur.

name: Breanne Barry
about: Lip-sync sensation who accrued more than 100,000 fans to her self-titled account. She also posted fact videos and collaborated with her siblings.

name: David Scarzone
about: Replaced former member Dalton Rapattoni to become the fifth member of the boy band IM5 in 2014, joining Dana Vaughns, Gabriel Morales, Cole Pendery, and Will Jay. He later left the band in early 2015.

name: Darzeth
about: YouTube gamer who is widely known for his XdarzethX channel's content. He has gained popularity there for his Roblox Let's Builds, tutorials, and playthroughs.

name: David Castro
about: Known for his childhood roles in such films as Where God Left His Shoes and 27 Dresses. He'd go on to star as Raphael Santiago in Freeform's Shadowhunters from 2016 until 2018.

name: Essence Atkins
about: Dee Dee Thorne from Half & Half who also played Suzanne Kingston on the short-lived series Are We There Yet? and starred in NBC's Marlon. As a film actress, she made an appearance in the 2009 movie Dance Flick.

name: Daniel Vermaak
about: Social media star who gained fame for his crowned danielxv_ TikTok channel. He rose to massive popularity for his stylish fashion worn while lip-syncing to popular music, including through duets.

name: Runlikeant
about: TikTok star who is best recognized for his runlikeant account where he posts comedy skits and dance videos, often involving his friends. He has accumulated over 950,000 followers on the platform. He shares dancing and comedic content on his runlikeant Instagram account.

name: Luke Johnson
about: Luke - or, as he is more commonly known, GameboyLuke - is a YouTube content creator of more than a decade who began his career on the video network by uploading Flash Animations when he was younger, moving onto Call of Duty Content in 2009, and then finally transitioning to Pokémon content in March 2013.

name: Dieter Bohlen
about: German songwriter and music producer best known for being a part of the group Modern Talking from 1984 to 1987 and from 1998 to 2003.

name: Steven Stamkos
about: NHL center who won the Maurice Rocket Richard Trophy as the league's top scorer in 2010 and 2012 with the Tampa Bay Lightning. He was selected first overall in the 2008 NHL Draft and soon after became one of the game's top offensive players.

name: John Posey
about: Film and television actor in addition to screenwriter and stage performer whose notable credits include Robocop 3, Manhunter and W.M.D. He wrote and starred in the 2010 film Legendary.

name: Ashleigh Butler
about: Best known for winning the reality series Britain's Got Talent following a dance performance with her mixed-breed dog, Pudsey, this television phenomenon later hosted a reality series called Who Let the Dogs Out?

name: Riyadh K
about: YouTuber who shot to fame when two of his videos, "Mom Reads Son's Grindr Messages" and "Gay Guy Calls Westboro Baptist Church," went viral in the span of two weeks. He is also one of Ireland's leading activists for LGBT rights and has been a radio host since the age of 17. He has been represented professionally by YMU Entertainment.

name: Jaden Hossler
about: TikTok star whose comedic videos and dance videos have earned him over 9 million fans. He is known for featuring other creators such as Chase Hudson, Griffin Johnson and Chase Keith in his posts. Also a singer under the artist name Jxdn, he released his debut single "Comatose" in March 2020. He featured rapper Machine Gun Kelly on his 2021 track "Wanna Be" and he has collaborated with Nessa Barrett on multiple songs.

name: Kairi Cosentino
about: Video creator on TikTok who has garnered more than 2 million fans to his kairi account. He has posted a mix of dance, comedy, lip-sync and other types of videos.

name: Reed Woehrle
about: Social star who has earned more than 2.2 million fans to his .reedwoehrle TikTok account. He gained his following on the platform for his frequent selfies and lip syncs. He also gained a following on Instagram with more than 390,000 followers.

name: Karina Garcia
about: Beauty and lifestyle vlogger who runs a popular self-titled YouTube channel, formerly called TheKarinaBear, where she posts hauls, DIYs, and makeup tutorials for her 9 million subscribers.

name: Alana Clements
about: Point-of-view style content creator who rose to fame by sharing a variety of videos on her alanaclem TikTok account. Her videos have received more than 131 million likes on the platform.

name: Bethany Hamilton
about: American surfer who became famous for continuing to compete professionally after losing her left arm to a 14 foot tiger shark when she was 13. She appeared as herself in the 2014 film Dolphin Tale 2.

name: Big Show
about: Self-described as the World's Largest Athlete, he became the first wrestler to hold the World Heavyweight, ECW World, WWE, and WCW World titles. His real name is Paul Wight. In 2020, he began starring on the Netflix series The Big Show Show.

name: Yasmyn Switzer
about: Instagram and YouTube star who uses her platforms to share her stories of teenage pregnancy and young motherhood. She has 105 million views on her YouTube channel.  She is represented by Select Management Group.

name: Klay Thompson
about: Guard/forward who was drafted 11th overall by the Golden State Warriors in 2011. He helped the team win NBA Championships in 2015, 2017 and 2018. He and Warriors teammate Stephen Curry became known as the "Splash Brothers" for their outside shooting abilities. In 2015, he was selected to his first career NBA All-Star game.

name: Jaliyah Monet
about: Popular social influencer who has amassed over 3.2 million subscribers to her Jaliyahma YouTube channel, where she posts a variety of fun videos, including challenges. She has also run social media accounts under the name Life of Jaliyah. The music video for her song "I Need You" with Funny Mike has received over 13 million views since it was released in October of 2018.

name: Molly Burke
about: Activist and motivational speaker who has advocated for the blind, speaking at We Day events across the world. She has received the Oakville YMCA Peace Award and served as the co-host for the weekly television show AMI This Week. She also runs a successful vlog on her self-titled YouTube channel.

name: I.N
about: JYP Entertainment trainee who is a member of the K-pop band Stray Kids. His real name is Yang Jeong-in.

name: James Dean
about: Starred in Rebel Without a Cause and East of Eden, then died in a 1955 car crash at a tragically young age. He became an icon of the disillusioned teenager.

name: Parker Yeager
about: Member of the Yeager family who rose to fame on the YouTube channel Shot of The Yeagers. The family channel has amassed more than 5 million subscribers with over 3.1 billion views.

name: Suede Brooks
about: Popular internet personality best known for her presence on TikTok and Instagram. She is known for her fashion and beauty content. She often posts clothing hauls and "Get Ready With Me" videos to her suedebrooks TikTok account, which has amassed over 1.4 million fans. She has been associated with the United Talent Agency.

name: Dani Harmer
about: Actress who stars as Tracy Beaker on the CBBC series The Story of Tracy Beaker, Tracy Beaker Returns, and Tracy Beaker Survival Files. She is also known for her lead role on the sitcom Dani's House and its spin-off Dani's Castle.

name: Curtis Pritchard
about: Professional ballroom and latin dancer and choreographer who joined the staff of professional dancers on Dancing with the Stars Ireland. His long-time dance partner is Emily Barker. In 2019, he competed on Love Island.

name: Nikki Glamour
about: Beauty and lifestyle YouTuber who's known for her storytime videos on her self-titled channel. She has accumulated more than 650,000 subscribers. She has advertised for the Team Blends company on her Instagram.

name: Anderson Paak
about: Hip-hop/R&B singer and rapper with a stage name of Anderson .Paak., he released an album titled Venice in October of 2014 and a follow-up album called Malibu in January of 2016. He is also one-half of the duo known as NxWorries.

name: Venus Angelic
about: British YouTuber known for her doll cosplay videos. She posts makeup tutorials and also the occasional food challenge video. She has often tested popular beauty products from asian countries and has also posted gaming videos for games like Minecraft.

name: Romell Henry
about: Famous for his collaboration with Jay Swingler on the popular TGFbro YouTube channel, he has contributed to numerous comedy videos, including "The Superglue Game," "Bathing in Nettles," and "Getting into Strangers' Cars." TGFbro has accumulated more than 6 million subscribers.

name: LosPollosTV
about: Twitch and YouTube gamer known for his NBA 2K videos, which focus on MyTeam pack openings and gameplay. He'd later become a part of the NBA 2K focused web group known as 2Hype and has also been a member of Luminosity Gaming. His YouTube channel has also featured pranks, challenges and trick shot videos.

name: Julio Jones
about: Star NFL wide receiver selected 6th overall in the 2011 NFL Draft by the Atlanta Falcons. He topped 1,000 receiving yards in just his second NFL season. In 2017, he helped lead the Falcons to Super Bowl LI. He began playing for the Tennessee Titans in 2021.

name: Kathryn Newton
about: Actress known for starring in Paranormal Activity 4 and later Pokémon: Detective Pikachu. She also played Louise Brooks on the CBS series Gary Unmarried a role that earned her the 2010 Young Artist Award for Best Supporting Young Actress in a TV series. In 2019, she began starring in Netflix's The Society.

name: Charlie Axel Woods
about: The son of legendary golf star Tiger Woods and Swedish model Elin Nordegren. He began golfing competitively himself, and won a junior golf tournament in Palm City, Florida in August 2020.

name: Caspian Slyfox
about: Born Caspian Harper Brown, he is the youngest in a family of four featured on the YouTube channel Slyfox Family. His parents created a side channel for him called Cas's Corner.

name: Mayra Isabel
about: Freelance makeup artist who gained fame for her MayraTouchOfGlam YouTube channel. She has earned more than 2.1 million subscribers by posting makeup tutorials, product reviews, and tag videos.

name: Nought
about: Born Frederick Alexander Pye and known as Fred Pye for short, he is a gamer on YouTube with the channel Nought. YouTube was a hobby for him for about two years before the release of Grand Theft Auto V, a game that helped him become a full-time professional YouTuber.

name: Chai Hansen
about: Thai-Australian actor who gained fame in the role of a merman named Zac Blakely on the series Mako: Island of Secrets.

name: Seth Green
about: Comedic actor who became known as Oz on Buffy the Vampire Slayer and won multiple Emmy Awards for creating and producing the television show Robot Chicken. His film credits include The Italian Job, Rat Race and Without a Paddle.

name: John Williams
about: One of cinema's all-time greatest composers who wrote the theme music for Star Wars, Superman, and Indiana Jones. He also composed one of the most recognized theme songs in history, for Jaws, which won the 1975 Academy Award for Best Original Dramatic Score.

name: Gary Coleman
about: Child star who became famous for his role on TV's Diff'rent Strokes, which in turn launched his career upwards before battles with health and finances struck.

name: Aashna Hegde
about: Indian Instagram star who usually posts selfies and lip sync videos to her account. She has accumulated over 1 million followers on her Instagram.

name: Stephanie Courtney
about: Known as Flo from the Progressive Insurance commercial advertisements, she's also had supporting film roles in Blades of Glory and The Heartbreak Kid.

name: Alec Golinger
about: Australian actor, model and singer who's appeared in campaigns for known brands such as Target, Kmart, Lee Jeans, Cotton On and Russell Athletics.

name: Lil Agz
about: Singer songwriter and rapper whose debut single was "Momma We Good." He rose to fame after a video of him telling a story about one of his friends went viral. He is known for using the phrase "Ohh Saylesss."

name: Emma Johansson
about: Content creator on YouTube with a channel simply called emma where she posts aesthetic how-to videos as well as DIY and morning routine content. She has earned more than 280,000 subscribers.

name: Vince Neil
about: Lead singer for Mötley Crüe who also had a successful solo career, releasing albums like Carved in Stone, Exposed, and Tattoos & Tequila.

name: Kimbo Slice
about: Street fighter who used internet fame to start a professional boxing and MMA career.

name: Sophie Bennett
about: Young Canadian actress known for her role as Stevie Lake on The Saddle Club. She also played a role in the 2002 film Salem Witch Trials.

name: Tommy Lyon
about: Singer on TikTok who has garnered more than 1.7 million followers to his tommylyon_ account. He primarily posted snippets of covers of popular songs. He also became a member of the UK-based band Here At Last, alongside Pedro Santos, Ryan Burns, James Thomas and Zach Loizou.

name: Creed Bratton
about: American television actor and former musician with the group The Grass Roots.

name: Br0
about: YouTube gaming personality who is famous for his Br0 channel and its content. He has gained popularity there for his Minecraft playthroughs, trolling videos, and montages.

name: Dante Myles Hoagland
about: American actor who has appeared in Fading Gigolo and 30 Rock. He played the role of Howie in the 2015 film Emelie.

name: Kacey Dirksen
about: American Instagram star who is best known for her lifestyle, fashion, and travel-related social media content. She has worked professionally as a model for various different print campaigns.

name: Justin Degryse
about: Pop music performer who rose to fame after competing on Belgium's The Voice Kids in 2020. This exposure has led to him amassing more than 100,000 Instagram followers.

name: Max Beaumont
about: Entrepreneur who founded his own company called Beaumont Studios. He created a social messaging app called Casso and later founded a penny auction site called SnapBidder.  He was previously in residence with the social media friend group Team 10 until August 2017.

name: Leoobalys
about: TikTok creator whose lip sync videos of German and American pop songs has earned her more than 1.3 million fans so far. She has also been known to create videos inspired by creators like Valy.

name: Bella Poarch
about: Popular social media star best known for her bellapoarch TikTok account where she posts comedy lip-sync videos, often about gaming. Her videos have earned her over 85 million followers on the app. She won the Breakout Creator award at the 2021 Streamy Awards. Also a singer, she signed a record deal with Warner Records in May 2021.

name: Michael B. Jordan
about: Actor who propelled to fame after starring as antagonist Erik Killmonger in Marvel's Black Panther. He first gained recognition for his role as Wallace on HBO's acclaimed drama The Wire and as Vince Howard on the NBC series Friday Night Lights. Other starring roles include Fruitvale Station, Chronicle, Creed, That Awkward Moment, and Fantastic Four.

name: Tom Hiddleston
about: Actor who played Loki in The Avengers and Thor films and starred in Woody Allen's Midnight in Paris. His role in The Avengers earned him the 2013 MTV Movie Awards for Best Fight and Best Villain.

name: Marco Hall
about: Boxer and popular social media star who is best recognized for his iammarcohall TikTok account where he posts comedy and prank videos. He has gained over 7 million followers on the platform.

name: Avan Jogia
about: Became known to television audiences as Beck Oliver on Nickelodeon's Victorious and appeared as the same character in the TV movie iParty With Victorious. He also played Finn in the 2012 Nickelodeon TV movie Rags. In 2019, he began starring in the Starz series Now Apocalypse as the lead character Ulysses.

name: DJ Prince
about: Son of popular YouTube stars, Damien Prince and Biannca Raines, who are best known for their D&B Nation channel. He is also featured on the family channel The Prince Family.

name: Kelli Berglund
about: Actress known as Bree on the Disney XD series Lab Rats. In 2014, she began playing the lead character, Mae Hartley, in How to Build a Better Boy. She'd go on to star on the family movie Going for Gold in 2018. In 2019, she began starring as Carly on Now Apocalypse alongside Tyler Posey.

name: Nas Daily
about: Short content creator named Nuseir Yassin who became known for making videos for AJ+. He would go on to create short one minute informational videos on his own Facebook page Nas Daily, which has earned more than 2 million followers. His videos are about both his life and the lives of those he meets on his travels worldwide. In November of 2021, he posted a video to Instagram explaining the Ship of Theseus paradox.

name: Jalen Green
about: 6'6" shooting guard who was selected second overall in the 2021 NBA Draft by the Houston Rockets. He was a 2020 McDonald's All-American following a standout senior year at Prolific Prep.

name: Eden Harvz
about: Popular social media star who is best recognized for the storytime, lip-sync, comedy and "eat with me" videos she posts to her edenharvzofficial TikTok account. Her fans have boosted her to over 2.7 million followers on the app.

name: Lewis Sharp
about: Lip-sync and comedy video creator on the platform TikTok who collaborates alongside his twin brother James on the account TheSharpTwins, which has earned over 5 million fans. He is a skilled dancer as well. A dance routine to an Eminem song gained him over 23 million views on TikTok.

name: Savannah Kristich
about: Dancer who represents and trains at The Rock Center for Dance in Las Vegas. In 2018 she was part of The Rock Company team on World of Dance season 2. They made the finals in the junior team division.

name: Jungwon
about: Pop singer who is best recognized as a member and leader of the boyband ENHYPEN. The band, which consists of seven members, was formed on the reality show I-LAND.

name: Giulia Amato
about: TikTok star who has risen to fame for her nobeefonlychicken channel. Her dances, lip syncs, and POV's often to trends popular on TikTok have helped her amass more than 68 million likes. She has been represented by the Evolve Model Management company.

name: Isabella Gómez
about: Colombian actress most famous for her role as Elena Alvarez on the Netflix original series One Day at a Time. She also stars as Isla in the 2019 movie A Cinderella Story: Christmas Wish.

name: Sunjai Williams
about: Dancer best known for her appearances on the dance competition reality show Bring It! She participated on the show as a member of the dance troupe Dancing Dolls.

name: Ashley Ortega
about: American YouTuber who has earned legions of fans with her challenges, games, stories, hauls, and more. She's also widely known on her ashleysortega Instagram with over 390,000 followers. She has posted numerous bikini and lingerie pictures on her Instagram page.

name: Johnny Suh
about: Rapper who made his debut as part of the SM Rookies SR14 B sub-unit. He went on to become a member of SM's project, NCT.

name: Hannah Bahng
about: Trending dance and lip-sync content creator who rose to fame by sharing performances on her self-titled TikTok account. She has more than 1.5 million followers on the platform. She has also been known posting her style and outfit photographs for her 600,000 followers on her hannahhbahng.

name: Social Repose
about: Electronic dance pop recording artist who first gained fame while posting original music, cover songs, vlogs and more to his Social Repose YouTube channel. In 2015, he released his first full-length album, Yalta, which featured the single "Island of Yours."

name: Drippiejay
about: Web star best known for his drippiejay TikTok account where he posts comedy, POV, and lip-sync videos that often feature his own music. He has accumulated over 1.1 million fans on the account. He has also been known to post outfit pictures on his drippiejay Instagram account.

name: Saquon Barkley
about: Running back who was selected 2nd overall in the 2018 NFL Draft by the New York Giants. He was named 2018 Rookie of the Year after compiling over 2,000 yards from scrimmage. During his college career at Penn State University, he was named the Big Ten Offensive Player of the Year in 2016 and 2017 and he was a Consensus All-American in 2017.

name: Joe Pesci
about: Iconic tough-guy actor who starred in the Martin Scorsese films Goodfellas, Raging Bull and Casino. His performance in Raging Bull earned him an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actor. He also played the title character in 1992's My Cousin Vinny and the dimwitted burglar in the Home Alone films.

name: Sage Bender
about: Photographer and professional Jiu-Jitsu fighter best recognized for his sxge.bender TikTok account where he posts comedy videos with his friends. He has earned over 260,000 followers on the platform.

name: Eloise Mitchell
about: Sister of web video star Jake Mitchell who became active on social media, particularly on her eloisemofficial Instagram account where she has amassed over 220,000 followers. She also gained popularity on YouTube with over 220,000 subscribers.

name: Chung-ha Kim
about: First seen as a competitor on Produce 101, she would join the short-lived K-pop girl group I.O.I before it disbanded in 2017. After the group dissolved, she became a host for Ah! Sunday - A Running Miracle. She later went on to become a solo artist and released her debut EP titled Hands on Me in June 2017.

name: Kendry Alonso
about: One of two young personalities to run the popular YouTube channel Keilly and Kendry. The channel became known for slime content, challenges and general vlogs.

name: Sophia Smith
about: English Instagram star who became known through her relationship with One Direction singer Liam Payne. She has over 900,000 followers on Instagram.

name: J2hundred
about: Popular TikTok star who is best known for the comedy and reaction videos he posts to his J2hundred account. His videos have earned him over 1.9 million followers on the social media platform.

name: Dakota Brooks
about: Social media sensation and influencer from New England who has gained strong followings on Instagram, Twitter, Snapchat, YouNow and Flurry. He has been featured in J14 teen magazine as well as Rolling Stone Magazine and Daydream Magazine.

name: CranberrySpriteChill
about: Gaming personality who incorporated her fandom for Roblox into her TikTok videos. Her comedy and other entertaining videos earned her more than 800,000 followers on her account cranberryspritechill.

name: James Sharp
about: Video creator on the TikTok account TheSharpTwins who publishes a mix of lip-sync and comedy videos with the help of his twin brother Lewis. They have accrued more than 5 million fans.

name: Charlie Day
about: Best known for playing the character Charlie Kelly on the popular FX series It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia, he also created the show and serves as a producer and writer alongside co-stars Glenn Howerton and Rob McElhenney.

name: nycjalen
about: TikTok star who has gained fame for his nycjalen account. He has garnered more than 550,000 followers for his comedic sketches and memes, which often highlight his Jamaican heritage.

name: Vicky Justiz
about: Fitness model and YouTube star best known for her self-titled channel where she has gained over 1.8 million subscribers posting exercise tips, guides, and how-to videos.

name: Harry Dawkins
about: Younger brother of 5 Seconds of Summer drummer Ashton Irwin.

name: Ashley Perkins
about: YouTuber best known as the "Perkyy" half of the channel Perkyy and HoneeyBee. Her reactions to music videos, viral videos and more have brought over 430,000 subscribers to her channel.

name: GreenLegoCats
about: Comedic gaming commentator with an all-things-Roblox channel on YouTube who has earned more than 500,000 subscribers to his greenlegocats123 account. His most watched videos are generally of the trolling variety.

name: James Smith
about: Singer and guitarist who was a finalist on series 8 of Britain's Got Talent.

name: Rose Leslie
about: Scottish actress best known for playing Ygritte on the HBO fantasy series Game of Thrones. She also appeared in the first season of Downton Abbey and in CBS's The Good Fight.

name: Chi With A C
about: English YouTube star who is known for post frequent vlogs, particularly in her pajamas. She has 490,000 subscribers and 37 million overall views.

name: James Owen Sullivan
about: Known by the nickname The Rev, he was a drummer and songwriter who performed with the heavy metal band Avenged Sevenfold.

name: Jakob Morales
about: TikTok star who is best recognized for his lip synch videos and effects driven videos where he often changes outfits mid shot. He is also known for his lifestyle content and shares videos with his friends and family for his over 650,000 followers as well.

name: Jayden Soto
about: TikTok video creator who implements music into each of his lip-sync, dance and comedy videos. His jaydennsoto account has more than 430,000 fans.

name: William Henry Harrison
about: Ninth president of the United States, the first to die in office, and the last to be born before the Declaration of Independence was written.

name: Alejandra Guzmán
about: Latin Grammy Award-winning singer and actress who released the hit single "Eternamente Bella." She has sold more than ten million albums over the course of her career.

name: ThatsBella
about: Filipino lifestyle and beauty vlogger who has earned more than 1.1 million subscribers creating vlogs, tutorials, hauls and Q&A videos. She has become recognized as a successful celebrity interviewer, with many of her videos featuring stars like Vice Ganda and Shaira Luna.

name: Eliza Hutton
about: Gained fame for being engaged to late actor Brandon Lee, son of Bruce Lee, up until his death in 1993. It was after his death that she began petitioning to tighten gun regulations on film sets.

name: Emma Roberts
about: Starred as Addie Singer on the Nickelodeon series Unfabulous and Madison Montgomery on American Horror Story: Coven. In 2007, she won a ShoWest Award for Female Star of Tomorrow and a Young Artist Award for Best Supporting Actress for her performance in Aquamarine. She was cast as Chanel Oberlin in the FOX comedy/horror series Scream Queens.

name: Chloë Grace Moretz
about: Vaulted to fame at a young age with her starring roles in Kick-Ass, Hugo, and Let Me In. She then went on to play Carrie in the 2013 remake of the film, Angie Steadman in 2010's Diary of a Wimpy Kid, and Mia Hall in 2014's If I Stay. She landed the role of Cassie Sullivan in the 2016 action film The 5th Wave.

name: FaZe Kay
about: Former director of the popular Call of Duty gaming group known as FaZe Clan who has attracted a subscriber count of more than 6 million to his YouTube channel.

name: Jordan Maron
about: YouTuber who became known for his CaptainSparklez channel, where he primarily uploads song parodies using video games such as Minecraft. His channel has over 11 million subscribers.

name: Vic Fuentes
about: Lead singer of the post-hardcore band Pierce The Veil, which gained fame for their 2007 album A Flair for the Dramatic.

name: Yara Shahidi
about: Best known for playing Zoey Johnson on the ABC series Black-ish and its spin-off Grown-ish. In 2009, she starred alongside Eddie Murphy in Imagine That and, in 2010, she played a role in the Angelina Jolie film Salt. She later starred in The Sun Is Also a Star in 2019.

name: Paisley McKnight
about: Second adopted child of Mindy and Shaun McKnight, the famous parents behind the YouTube channel Cute Girls Hairstyles. She was featured in the "Paisley GRADUATES from Elementary School | Behind the Braids Ep 145" video from June of 2021.

name: Holly Willoughby
about: English television host of The Voice UK, This Morning, and Celebrity Juice, she has hosted a number programs on BBC One and ITV.

name: Stephanie Beatriz
about: One of the stars of Fox's Emmy award-winning comedy Brooklyn Nine-Nine in the role of Detective Rosa Diaz. She was also featured in the critically-acclaimed independent film Short Term 12.

name: Milo Winter
about: Became a popular TikTok personality with over 120,000 fans on his milowinter account. He first gained traction on TikTok under the username milosokhowru. He has also posted livestreams, Q&A's and other vlog content on his MilosOkay YouTube channel.

name: Elizabeth Banks
about: Actress who has played prominent roles in the films Seabiscuit, The 40-Year-Old Virgin, Magic Mike XXL, The Hunger Games and Man on a Ledge. She also starred in Pitch Perfect and Pitch Perfect 2 and provided her voice for The Lego Movie.

name: Princess Tommi
about: Social media star who has gained fame for her princess tommi YouTube channel. Her beauty and relationship vlogging alongside story times and mukbangs have helped her garner massive popularity. She has been featured in magazines like LV Magazine Teen and Sheen Magazine.

name: Lee Carson
about: Best known as the right hand man, or best Minecraft helper, of Joseph Garrett, he goes by the names L for Leeeeee x, Lee Bear, or Leematode. He has earned over 360,000 subscribers on his YouTube channel.

name: CalebCity
about: Comedy content creator on Vine who earned more than 460,000 followers before the app was discontinued. Several of his videos commented on situations in everyday life. He also gained a following on YouTube, where his vlogs and comedy videos have earned him more than 4.4 million subscribers.

name: Seulgi
about: Lead vocalist and dancer of the South Korean K-pop group Red Velvet. She has also appeared on television shows such as Descendants of the Sun, Let's Go! Dream Team, The Last Song and Off to School.

name: Bradley Colburn
about: Deemed the King of the YouTube Walkthrough by FMV Magazine, he plays the latest and most popular video game titles and publishes his walkthroughs to his enormously popular channel TheRadBrad.

name: Hailey Sigmond
about: Lip-sync and dance video creator who has accrued more than 950,000 fans. She has posted videos with friends and family at home and at school.

name: Elliott Brown
about: English model who is known for having earned representation from several different modeling agencies including Wilhelmina London and Above & Beyond Los Angeles. He shares additional modeling portraits through his Instagram for his over 20,000 followers.

name: Rob Czar
about: Famous as a producer of DIY videos on the popular ThreadBanger YouTube channel, this web star has earned over 3.8 million subscribers on Threadbanger and more than 1 million subscribers on his personal Rob Czar channel.

name: Makenzie Vega
about: Played Grace Florrick on the CBS series The Good Wife, for which she and the cast received a nomination for a Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble.

name: Brianna Mizura
about: Content creator who has gained popularity for the acting POVs she posts to her brianna_mizura TikTok account. She portrays several different characters and releases her videos like television show episodes. She has gained over 2.8 million followers on the social media app.

name: Don Omar
about: Nicknamed El Ray, he is a reggaeton singer best known for his 2006 album King of Kings. He has also appeared in a number of films in the Fast & Furious franchise, including Tokyo Drift and Fast Five.

name: Monica Church
about: YouTube content creator who loves posting content about all things makeup, fashion, beauty, and film to her channel hairodynamic.

name: Donny Pangilinan
about: One of five kids born to Filipino comedian and actress Maricel Laxa. Also an actor, he landed a lead role on the TV series He's Into Her.

name: Shelby Church

In 2013, she began playing the character Polly Gray on the TV series Peaky Blinders and in 2019 she starred alongside Richard Gere in BBC's MotherFatherSon.

name: YourRAGE

name: Taissa Farmiga

name: Paige

name: Robert De Niro

name: Joyner Lucas

name: Donnie Wahlberg

name: Austin Waller

name: Lil B

name: Lincoln Hoellein

name: qwerticorn

name: Kia Pegg

name: Rhys Herbert

name: Jordan Jones

name: Lily Rabe

name: SSN Santa

name: Alexys Nycole Sanchez

name: Godo

name: Chosen Jacobs

name: Ashleyosity
