name: Luiza Cordery
about: YouTube beauty guru who is widely known for her Luiza's Channel content. She has gained popularity there for her beauty supply hauls, makeup tutorials, and original vocal covers of popular songs.

name: Sebastian Danzig
about: Best known as the guitarist for the Canadian art-rock band Palaye Royale, he and lead singer Remington Leith were named champions of MTV's Musical March Madness in 2014. Their single "Get Higher" was also chosen for an internationally distributed Samsung Galaxy Note commercial.

name: Young B
about: Recurring cast member of the VH1 reality series Love & Hip Hop: New York since 2015 who became more well known almost a decade prior when she appeared alongside DJ Webstar on his 2006 debut album Webstar Presents: Caught in the Web.

name: Ria Ricis
about: Founder of the hijab line Ricis Style, she is a widely successful social media phenomenon who went viral for her daily tutorials on hijab style and inspiration. She has amassed a whopping 26 million Instagram followers to her riaricis1795 account.

name: Kolton Stewart
about: Well known for his role on the television series Some Assembly Required in the role of Jarvis, he played a lead singer in the feature film Isabelle Dances Into the Spotlight. He is also a recording artist and dancer.

name: Olivia de Havilland
about: Actress who portrayed the gentle Melanie Hamilton in Gone with the Wind. Her performance in the 1946 film To Each His Own earned her an Academy Award for Best Actress.

name: Dan Aykroyd
about: Saturday Night Live and The Blues Brothers star who gained fame in Ghostbusters and was nominated for an Academy Award for for Driving Miss Daisy.

name: Enzo Tais-Toi
about: Social star known for his prank videos and vlogs on YouTube. He is also extremely popular on TikTok with over 2.6 million fans on his enzotaistoi account.

name: Jeven Reliford
about: TikTok star and singer who has earned over 3.5 million fans to his jeven.reliford TikTok account where he primarily posts videos of himself singing. He is also known for his self-titled Instagram account, where he posts lifestyle photos from his everyday life, including those depicting his track career.

name: Anna Catify
about: 2017 Shorty Awards nominee for Best Muser who would showcase her artistic ability on TikTok with her time-lapses of drawings, paintings and character makeup. She would often do lip-sync videos as well for her more than 12 million fans. She also became a TikTok representative and earned the verification crown as well as badges for art and talent.

name: Andre Braugher
about: Emmy-nominated television actor known for his role as Detective Frank Pembleton on Homicide: Life on the Street. In 2013 he began portraying Captain Ray Holt in the series Brooklyn Nine-Nine.

name: Sosaidsteph
about: Variety content creator on TikTok who is recognized for posting point-of-view style videos on his self titled. His personality helped him amass more than 500,000 followers.

name: Leeteuk
about: South Korean singer, actor, and television host who gained fame while in the band Super Junior, as well as the subgroups called Super Junior-T and Super Junior-H.

name: Margot Robbie
about: Australian actress who first gained recognition for playing Donna Brown on the soap opera Neighbours from 2008 until 2011. She then went on to star in the American films The Wolf of Wall Street and Focus. Additionally, she nabbed the titular role in the Oscar-nominated film I, Tonya and played Queen Elizabeth in Mary Queen of Scots.

name: Lindsay Lohan
about: Actress who first gained recognition for portraying Annie James and Hallie Parker, twins separated shortly after birth, in the 1998 Disney comedy The Parent Trap. She won several MTV Movie Awards for her starring role in Mean Girls in 2004 and she also played lead roles in Herbie: Fully Loaded and Freaky Friday.

name: Ashley Tisdale
about: Actress and singer best known for her role as Maddie on Disney's The Suite Life of Zack & Cody. She has won several acting awards, including an MTV Movie Award, for her performances in the High School Musical films. She also voices the character Candace on Phineas and Ferb. In 2020, she became a panelist on The Masked Dancer.

name: Saweetie
about: Rapper, songwriter, actress and designer with a debut single titled "Icy Grl." The Poster Child-directed music video for the song was watched 3.5 million times on YouTube in 3 weeks and earned her praise from Vibe Magazine, XXL, HipHopDX, and MTV UK as an artist to watch in 2018.

name: Mikey Barone
about: Popular social media influencer who initially found an audience on YouNow before branching out into Instagram and YouTube.

name: Alex Morgan
about: U.S. soccer forward who received international fame for scoring the dramatic game-winning goal in the semi-finals of the 2012 Summer Olympics. She also helped the U.S. women's team win the 2015 and 2019 World Cups.

name: Jackson Dean
about: Point-of-view style content creator best known for sharing lip sync performances on his self-titled TikTok account. The bulk of his videos are set to popular rap and pop songs. His charismatic personality has led to him amassing more than 4.9 million fans.

name: Jenni Rivera
about: Born Dolores Janney Rivera, she became immortalized for her 2008 album Jenni, which hit #1 on the US Billboard 200. She died in a plane crash in 2012.

name: 757cece
about: Dancing enthusiast who would show off her talents via Dubsmash and Instagram videos, earning more than 2.2 million followers for her content on the latter platform.

name: Ruth B
about: Canadian singer who first became known as Vine star. She released her debut album EP, The Intro, in November of 2015. By the time Vine was shut down, she had more than 2 million followers.

name: William Singe
about: Solo artist since April of 2015 who released a single called "The Jump Off" and a mixtape titled The Re-Introduction II. He was formerly a member of the five-piece boy band The Collective, which competed on the fourth season of The X Factor (Australia) in 2012 and finished in third place.

name: Caitlin Carmichael
about: Child actress who gained fame for her supporting roles in Backlight and Lizzie. She later played Kyra Devore in the TV mini-series Bag of Bones and Laney on the web series Chicken Girls. In 2017, she starred in A Mermaid's Tale.

name: Zaid Ali
about: YouTube sensation known for his channel ZaidAliT, where he posts comedy videos as well as video blogs about topical issues. His videos often deal with Desi culture. He has partnered with the company Manscaped and posted a video praising their products on his zaidalit Instagram.

name: Corie Rayvon
about: Model who became known for her previous relationship with web video star Khalil Underwood. She later created her own self-titled channel, which features reaction videos, pranks, and more. She has also worked as a brand ambassador for companies like Fashion Nova and Unice Hair Extensions.

name: MyFroggyStuff
about: Content creator named Latoya Moore-Broyles who is behind the YouTube channel MyFroggyStuff, which became a mother-daughter collaborative doll and toy crafting channel. Her 2.5 million subscribers would tune in to watch her DIY doll crafting content which featured products from franchises such as Barbie, American Girl, Monster High, Shopkins and more. Her second YouTube channel is called CreateSomethingFabulous.

name: Sulivan Gwed
about: French social media personality with over 1.6 million YouTube subscribers and more than 1.2 million Instagram followers.

name: Justin McNease
about:
Comedic personality on TikTok who became known for both his skits and vlog-like content. He has accrued more than 4.8 million followers for his justinsske
account.

name: Sebastián Javier
about: YouTube sensation who caught his first break after launching his channel ThatSpanishBoy. He began doing regular shows on YouNow, providing him with a platform to quickly grow his fan base. His debut single, "Looking For Love," was released on November 2, 2015 and hit number one on the iTunes charts in less than 2 hours upon being released.

name: Branden Bingham
about: Family vlogger who lets viewers into his life as a husband and father on his This Is How We Bingham YouTube channel. He is famous for his #GoProFamily series, where he and his family document adventurous activities like skydiving and offroading using GoPro cameras.

name: Reese Hatala
about: Featured on the YouTube channel DanceOn, she is a dancing prodigy who took the internet by storm thanks to her unbelievable dancing ability at less than 10 years old. She became a member of the Will Adams' immaBEAST Dance Company.

name: Chrisandthemike
about: YouTube phenomenon named Christopher Foltz but best known as Chrisandthemike who produces creative video game content for over 1.3 million subscribers. He created series called Minecraft Solo, Minecraft Family, and Minecraft Comes Alive.

name: Burna Boy
about: Nigerian vocalist and songwriter known for Afrobeat, reggae, and dancehall albums as L.I.F.E. and Burn Notice. He was the recipient of a 2013 Nigeria Entertainment Award.

name: Bret Hart
about: Known as Bret "The Hitman" Hart, he was a five-time WWF World Heavyweight Champion and two-time WCW World Heavyweight Champion over the course of his 20-plus year career.

name: Presley Gerber
about: Eldest child and son of supermodel Cindy Crawford and her husband, businessman Rande Gerber. He has over 80,000 followers on Instagram.

name: Stunna Girl
about: Digital media influencer turned hip hop personality with notable singles called "Real Rap" and "On the Record," the latter of which was published to the YouTube channel Proxclusiv M.

name: Geoff Wigington
about: Lead guitarist and back up vocalist of the band Waterparks. The group released an EP called Black Light in 2014.

name: Mark Bontempo
about: Popular social media star who is best recognized for his mark.bontempo TikTok account where he has accumulated over 320,000 followers. He gained a great deal of publicity when he dated JoJo Siwa in 2020.

name: Sophie Clough
about: YouTube content creator who found quick success on the network, gaining close to 20,000 subscribers in just her first two months of uploading videos. She now has over 180,000 subscribers.

name: Jocelyn Amparo Flores
about: Teen suicide victim who rose to prominence after her untimely death was used as the basis for two of the late rapper Xxxtentacion's songs. "Garette's Revenge" and "Jocelyn Flores" were both about and dedicated to the young woman.

name: Xavier Martin
about: Popular social media star and content creator who is best recognized for the comedy videos he posts to his Xaviermartinnn_ TikTok account. He often recreates scenes from movies and television. He has gained over 3.3 million followers on the app.

name: Nikolai Hauck
about: Content creator on TikTok notable for his POV and relatable comedy videos. He has accrued more than 1.2 million fans for his nikoha account.

name: Cole Giannasca
about: Vlogger on YouTube and lifestyle influencer on Instagram who would earn more than 50,000 followers on the latter network.

name: Desi Des
about: Popular content creator who posts prank and storytime videos to her DESI DES YouTube channel. Her videos have earned her over 210,000 subscribers on the platform.

name: Vince Staples
about: Notable for his 2015 album Summertime and for his 2014 EP Hell Can Wait, this West Coast rapper also released a number of early mixtapes, including Shyne Coldchain Vols. 1 & 2 and Stolen Youth. He has more than 1.2 million followers on Twitter.

name: Larry David
about: Producer and writer of the hit NBC series Seinfeld, which ran from 1989 to 1998. He then became the creator, writer, and lead actor on HBO's Curb Your Enthusiasm in 2000.

name: Danny Griffin
about: Television and film actor who is best recognized for his role as Sky in the Netflix series Fate: The Winx Saga. He has also appeared as the character Shane in Get Even.

name: Tom Zanetti
about: Club promoter and DJ who started up a nightclub called Insomnia before working with Club Mission in Leeds, winner of the Leeds Best Night Club award. He also runs the events company called Sleepin is Cheatin.

name: Demi Jones
about: British reality star who is best known for her appearance in 2020 on the UK's hit reality series Love Island. She also has a well known Instagram page featuring lifestyle, modeling, and travel content.

name: Sierra Sprague
about: YouTuber whose channel has become a home for vlogs, skits, and challenge videos. She has amassed over 340,000 subscribers. She joined a dance group called Turn Up Gang with Priceless Da Roc, Dmac and others. She was previously in a dance group called Yang Gang. She also posts dance videos on her sierra.sprague TikTok account, where she has amassed over 550,000 followers.

name: Olivia Kay
about: Known through her YouTube covers of numerous popular songs, this young singer quickly attracted more than 40,000 subscribers and over 6 million views on the platform. She released a single called "You're One in a Million" in June of 2015.

name: Olivia Occhigrossi
about: Beauty queen who was crowned Miss Teen America 2018. She previously won Miss Florida Teen America 2017 en route to her Miss Teen America title.

name: Peter Kay
about: English comedian who was first introduced to audiences when he won Channel 4's So You Think You're Funny? contest in 1997. His last stand-up comedy tour, where he played for over 1.2 million people, was entered into the Guinness Book of World Records as the most successful of all time.

name: Alex Brooks
about: YouTuber best known for his main channel MarzBar, where he posts comedy content for over 650,000 subscribers. He also runs a tech channel called TechFlow.

name: Canon Curry
about: Boy most famous for being the third child of multiple-time NBA MVP Stephen Curry and television chef Ayesha Curry.

name: Jackson Odell
about: Actor turned singer-songwriter who first rose to fame playing Zeke in the film adaptation of Judy Moody and the Not Bummer Summer. He was also known as Ari on the TV Show The Goldbergs.

name: Johnny Weir
about: Figure skater who starred in his own show called Be Good Johnny Weir. He took home the bronze medal at the 2008 World Championships in the men's singles competition and was a two-time Grand Prix Final bronze medalist.

name: Ayiana Randolph
about: Popular social media star who is best recognized for the choreography videos she posts to her radical420dudee TikTok account. She has accumulated over 600,000 followers on the app.

name: Brandon Stewart
about: TikTok star known for his dance videos and lip-syncs. He has earned more than 900,000 followers on his bdotsdot22 account.

name: Brooklyn Queen
about: Rapper who became a viral sensation with the release of her 2017 music video "Keke Taught Me." She is also the creative force behind songs like "Beat the Baby" and "Pretty Girl Stuff."

name: Tom Cruise
about: Actor who won Golden Globe Awards for his roles in Born on the Fourth of July, Jerry Maguire, and Magnolia. He had his breakthrough role in the 1983 film Risky Business and in 1996, he began playing Ethan Hunt in the popular Mission: Impossible film series.

name: Corinne Joy
about: Dancer and model who is a 3x national champion. She runs a self-titled YouTube channel where she uploads behind-the-scenes videos of her auditions, as well as footage of her different competitions.

name: Jason Genao
about: Actor who rose to widespread fame for his role on the Netflix original series The Get Down as Napoleon beginning in 2016. He has also starred on the Netflix original series On My Block as Ruby Martinez.

name: Valeria Arguelles
about: Social media star who has gained fame for her self-titled YouTube channel. She has earned massive popularity for her personal adventure, lifestyle, and fashion vlogging. She posted her "SURPRISING MY BOYFRIEND IN COLLEGE AFTER A MONTH AND A HALF OF NOT SEEING HIM" video in November of 2019 and has since received over 2.1 million views on it.

name: Andrea Barber
about: Teen screen actress of the 1990s who played the memorable role of Kimmy Gibbler on Full House and the character of Jennifer in the film Do You Remember Love. She signed on to reprise her role as Kimmy Gibbler in the 2016 Netflix follow-up series to Full House, Fuller House.

name: PartyNextDoor
about: Canadian vocalist who released his first studio album, PartyNextDoor Two, in July of 2014. The album peaked at number nineteen on Canadian music charts and at number fifteen on American charts and was, for a time, the number one R&B recording among American listeners.

name: Mia McKenna-Bruce
about: Actress best known as Tee Taylor in the Tracy Beaker Survival Files and Tracy Beaker Returns. She also played Ashley Tyler in the 2009 science fiction movie The Fourth Kind. In 2019, she began starring as Marilka in Netflix's fantasy drama The Witcher.

name: Elle King
about: Alternative pop singer whose music encompasses a variety of genres including blues and rock n' roll. Her debut album Love Stuff was certified Gold and her debut single "Ex's & Oh's" was nominated for two Grammy Awards in 2016.

name: Olivia Munn
about: Actress, model, pinup girl and star of the HBO series The Newsroom. In 2012, she appeared in the comedy film Magic Mike. She portrays Maya in the 2016 comedy Ride Along 2.

name: Thomas Gibson
about: Best known for portraying Dharma's uptight lawyer husband, Greg, on the sitcom Dharma & Greg, he's also known for roles on the CBS dramas Chicago Hope and Criminal Minds.

name: Sebastian Vettel
about: Dominant Formula One driver who won four straight World Championships from 2010 to 2013. He signed with Ferrari in 2015 and was named runner-up in 2017 and 2018 in the Formula One World Championships.

name: Skylar Marie
about: Social media personality, model and makeup artist who launched her own Skylar Marie Cosmetics & Beauty brand. She's extremely popular on Instagram where she posts beauty pics and clips for over 220,000 followers.

name: Sara Waisglass
about: Model and actress who landed her most prevalent role on the long-running series Degrassi: The Next Generation as Frankie Hollingsworth. She played the same character in Degrassi: Next Class, which started its run in 2016.

name: Nathan Doan
about: Comedic personality on both TikTok and YouTube who specializes in videos targeting Asian stereotypes. He is the creator of the character Ging Ging.

name: Itspeytonbabyy
about: American TikTok star who is best known for her popular lifestyle, dance, and lip-sync-oriented video clip content. She also has a popular Instagram account featuring more lifestyle, fashion, and travel content.

name: Rosie Rivera
about: Actress best known for her starring appearance on the reality show Rica, Famosa, Latina.

name: GoryGaming
about: Gamer who uploaded primarily Roblox and The Sims 4 content to her channel gorygaming24601. She has earned more than 160,000 subscribers and has also posted Gacha videos.

name: Dashiel
about: YouTube gamer who has gained widespread popularity for her gameplay walkthrough videos, which include Minecraft, Overwatch, and Grand Theft Auto V.

name: Patrick Wilson
about: Actor best known for his work in drama. His credits include Watchmen, Little Children, Insidious, and The Conjuring. He also portrayed Joe Pitt in the HBO miniseries Angels in America.

name: Matty Mullins
about: Lead vocalist and keyboard player for the American metalcore group Memphis May Fire who are based out of Dallas, Texas.

name: Chad Nazam
about: Sneaker collector who vlogs and showcases his sneakers on a self-titled YouTube channel to more than 140,000 subscribers.

name: Kendelle Cooper
about: Aspiring artist who became a TikTok sensation through her drawing videos on the app, earning over 900,000 followers. She is known on the web as Kendelle.C.

name: LaToya J. Jackson
about: Rose to fame first starring on the 27th season of The Real World: St. Thomas. This then earned her a spot on the 25th season of MTV's The Challenge: Free Agents. She has since become a presenter for Da Blacktop Radio.

name: Mahak Hamid
about: TikTok star who is best recognized for her dancing videos and lip synch content. She is also known for her comedy videos and clips featuring the artwork in her house which she shares for her over 1.6 million fans.

name: Chris Sutherland
about: Short-form skit content creator and educational TikTok personality who rose to fame through the use of his sutherlandphys account. He has garnered more than 2.1 million followers on the platform.

name: Tyler Funk
about: Member of the widely successful Funk Bros YouTube channel, who demonstrates his talent as a scooter rider and avid trampoline user. He also quickly surmounted more than 120,000 subscribers and growing on his personal YouTube channel.

name: Nathalia Ramos
about: Actress and singer who played Yasmin in Bratz: The Movie, and appeared in an episode of Nickelodeon's True Jackson, VP. In 2013, she played Jill in the film The Damned.

name: Mitchell Straub
about: Sometimes known as Mitchy, Straub, or more commonly by his YouTube name Strauberryjam, he is a Minecraft gamer with 3 channels by the names of StrauberryPlays, StrauberryVlogs, and the aforementioned Strauberryjam.

name: Jenna Dave
about: Crowned TikTok creator from the United States whose lip syncing skills have brought more than 440,000 fans to her ItsJennaDave TikTok account.

name: Gymnast Karina
about:
Gymnast, cheerleader, dancer and brand ambassador whose gymnastic photos and videos on Instagram have earned her more than 100,000 followers.
She has promoted leotard brands, gymnastic equipment and sportswear for SportsDirect, Nike, Gymnova, CannonsUK, Gymnastic Planet and Gymblocks.

name: Benedict Wong
about: British actor known for playing Ravel in Prometheus and Bruce Ng in The Martian. He also appeared as Kublai Khan in the Netflix series Marco Polo and starred as Master Lin in Syfy's Deadly Class. He played Wong in the Marvel film Doctor Strange.

name: Mateo Haack

In total, the channels earned more than 3 million subscribers, with their most popular ¡Hoy no hay cole! earning 2.8 million subscribers.

name: Mike Ryan
about: Country singer, songwriter, and guitarist who is known for his hit singles "New Hometown", "Bad Reputation", and "Wasting No More Whiskey". He earned representation from the Sea Gayle Music label.

name: Fie Laursen
about: Top Scandinavian blogger who writes about fashion, traveling, and lifestyle. She is also an aspiring singer, having recorded in Los Angeles previously.

name: Aaleeyah Petty
about: Social media star on Twitter and Instagram who is a fitness enthusiast. She was also popular on Vine.

name: Cole Carrigan
about: Professional makeup artist who is known for his elaborate designs often for high fashion events or specializing in FX makeup. He shares portraits and photos of his designs through Instagram for his over 330,000 followers.

name: Natsumiii
about: Chinese-born Canadian best known for her YouTube channel Sweetiebutt as well as her Twitch live stream account LoLNatsumiii where she streams League of Legends gameplay.

name: Theresa Magnus
about: Famous as the mother of actor and social media personality Gavin Magnus. She has helped manage her son's career, and appeared across his social media channels.

name: Riki Westmoreland
about: Television and film actress who is best known for her role as Mother in the Dhar Mann miniseries. She has also appeared in Daydreamer's Reality and Two Nations.

name: ForeverKi3rra
about: YouTube vlogger whose self-titled channel has earned more than 220,000 subscribers through a collection of GRWM videos, hauls, and, of course, vlogs.

name: Isaac Gonzalez
about: Social media influencer who has earned over 10,000 followers to his http.isaac Instagram account through his selfies and comedy posts.

name: Habiba Da Silva
about: Beauty blogger and content creator for YouTube who can be found online under the username LifeLongPercussion. She frequently creates beauty videos of Hijab style.

name: Julian Assange
about: WikiLeaks founder who exposed the secret files of many countries, creating much havoc in the international intelligence community.

name: River Woollard
about: Became known as an Australian child model through her appearances in advertisements for companies such as Indiemae, Feather Drum and Hux Baby.

name: Suzy Berhow
about: YouTube personality known for being part of the internet sensation Game Grumps. She also runs the channels Mortem3r and Kitty Kat gaming.

name: Butrint Imeri
about: R&B artist known for early projects called "Superwoman" and "Qu po dalim." His fame grew after his collaboration with the duo Blunt & Real on the song "Ki me lyp."

name: Reed Lewis
about: Popular TikTok star who is best known for his reeder04 account where he posts comedy videos, often involving his friends. He has gained over 650,000 followers on the platform.

name: Sophie Fergi
about: Social star and actress who rose to fame after getting cast on Brat TV's web series Mani. She's also appeared on the series Piperazzi. She has earned over 1.6 million subscribers to her self-titled YouTube channel by primarily posting comedic challenge videos. Many of her videos include friends of hers such as Piper Rockelle.

name: Post Malone
about: Rapper best known for his debut single "White Iverson," which he followed up with songs called "Too Young," "Holyfield" and "Tears." He is also talented as a singer, producer and guitarist.

name: Sydney Serena
about: YouTube beauty and fashion guru known for her self-titled channel. She has earned more than 2.3 million subscribers creating routines, vlogs, DIYs, and more.

name: Jasmine Gonzalez
about: Lip syncing TikTok creator who has earned more than 5 million followers to her jasminexgonzalez account. She's created videos set to songs by Daya, Zach Clayton, Shawn Mendes, among others. She has also been a youth ambassador for the anti-bullying organization Free2luv.

name: Harrison Osterfield
about: Popular in the social media world, he earned his first credited role in George Clooney's show Catch-22. He has earned more than 1 million followers on Instagram due to his close friendship with actor Tom Holland.

name: Lui Calibre
about: YouTube phenomenon who runs a popular self-titled channel, formerly called YourHeroes. He primarily posts Grand Theft Auto gameplay and is well known for pranking and trolling other players. His "GTA 5 Online Heists - All Heist Vehicles Unlocked (Valkyrie, Savage and Hydra Jet)" video has received over 14 million views since it was posted on March of 2015.

name: Malia Obama
about: Oldest daughter of the 44th president of the United States, Barack Obama. Obama published a letter to her and her sister Sasha in Parade magazine, saying that he wanted her to grow up as a compassionate person with no limits on her dreams.

name: McCreamy
about: Video gaming sensation on YouTube who plays games including Fortnite and Overwatch. He has racked up more than 5 million subscribers. His "Fortnite's Kinda Dying" parody music video has received over 59 million views since it was posted in April of 2020.

name: Alexus Oladi
about: Nicknamed Giggles, she is a dancer who would join the Abby Lee Dance Company mini team and be featured in season six of Dance Moms. She was a 4-time national champion by the age of eight and won Mini Female Dancer of the Year at the 2015 Hollywood Vibe Nationals in Las Vegas.

name: AnEsonGib
about: FIFA gamer on YouTube whose FIFA content consists of pack openings, challenges, ultimate teams, and more. He has also competed in popular boxing matches against other internet celebrities. He has posted multiple videos commenting on his own fights.

name: Fredo Santana
about: Tattooed Chicago rapper who was the CEO of Glory Boys Entertainment and Savage Squad Records. He was known for his contributions to the Trap genre of music and he released his debut album Trappin' Ain't Dead in 2014.

name: Cash Noguchi
about: Otherwise known as the Variety King, he is a TikTok superstar with a following of more than 3.6 million fans to his imstillcash account, formerly cash and mymiddlenameiscash. He has built his following through a wide range of videos, from transitions to lip syncs to a variety of comedic posts.

name: Safaree Samuels
about: Co-executive producer on Nicki Minaj's album Pink Friday: Roman Reloaded who had a long-standing friendship/relationship with Minaj for more than 12 years until turmoil arose.

name: Gage Gomez
about: American social media star who usually posts modeling photos to his im_gage Instagram account. He has gained over 600,000 followers on his Instagram account. In 2020, he joined the collaborative TikTok group OT House. He has also posted "study with me" videos on his Im_gage YouTube channel.

name: Julia Gilman
about: YouTuber whose beauty and fashion videos have earned her over 2.3 million subscribers on her BeautyTakenIn channel. She is known for posting DIY videos and also posts pranks, challenges and comedy videos. She also created the JUL SWIM swimwear company.

name: Clinton Cave
about: Guitarist, vocalist, saxophonist, and producer for the Australian alternative pop-rock band Chase Atlantic. The band's YouTube channel has earned over 1.2 million subscribers. They signed with Warner Brothers Records. In 2017, they released the hit song "Church."

name: Tayden Dyches
about: Widely known for being the eldest child featured on his Dyches Fam YouTube channel. He has gained popularity there alongside his three siblings, mother, and father for vlogs detailing their everyday lives. He's also had his own self-titled channel.

name: Kayco
about: Social star named Kayla Conley who is the creator of the YouTube channel Kayco which features challenge and prank videos as well as vlogs. She earned 850,000 subscribers.

name: Angelique Boyer
about: French-Mexican actress who became popular for her roles in the Mexican telenovelas Rebelde, Muchachitas Como Tú, and Corazón Salvaje. She also starred in Abismo de Pasión and Amar a muerte.

name: Era Istrefi
about: Famous for such popular singles as "Mani për Money," "E Dehun," and "A Po Don," this Videofest Award-winning Kosovar vocalist became known for combining elements of electronic, pop, and reggae music in her recordings and for writing most of her lyrics in the Kosovar Gheg Albanian dialect.

name: Daniela Nieves
about: Nickelodeon star best known for her role on the fantasy television series Every Witch Way.

name: Amara Que Linda
about: Social media star who rose to popularity for her self-titled YouTube channel where she's amassed more than 8 million subscribers for her entertaining vlogging. She's also popular on TikTok, earning more than 16 million fans for her lip-syncing and trending dance routines.

name: Mike Sorrentino
about: Known as "The Situation," he is a muscle-bound former reality star on MTV's Jersey Shore. He has come out with a clothing line, a work out DVD, Devotion Vodka, and Reebok and Zigtech shoes.

name: Alyssa Miller
about: Fashion model who has shot for Vogue, Elle, and the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Edition. She has also modeled for companies like Guess and Victoria's Secret.

name: Bill Withers
about: American singer-songwriter known for songs such as "Ain't No Sunshine," "Lean on Me," "Lovely Day," and "Just the Two of Us." He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2015.

name: Lilly Sabri
about: Fitness influencer who uses her background as a physiotherapist to teach the HIIT class known as Lean With Lilly. She has run bootcamps all over the world and worked with high-profile soccer teams like Everton FC, Chelsea FC and the English women's national team.

name: Kayden Gaulden
about: First son of famous American rapper NBA YoungBoy.

name: Kid Trunks
about: Vietnamese-American rapper also known as YoungBoiTrunks who would join a music collective called Members Only. Singles of his have included "Flex!" "Jack Frost!" "Underwater Trunks" and "Mustard Gold."

name: Nicholas Tyler
about: Content creator on TikTok responsible for the videos on the account tylerrniic. He has posted lip-sync content for his more than 190,000 fans while always trying to make his content happy and inspirational for others.

name: Celina Sharma
about: Singer who has risen to fame for her self-titled YouTube channel. She has earned massive popularity as a pop singer for sharing her original songs and travel vlogs.

name: Alex Hibbert
about: Child actor who starred as Little, the youngest version of Chiron, in the Academy Award-winning film Moonlight. He would go on to star as Kevin in the Showtime drama The Chi in 2018.

name: Icy Wyatt
about:
Short-form content creator on TikTok who is known for sharing lip-sync performances, lifestyle content and more. He has more than 650,000 followers and 11 million likes on his
luvwyatt account. He has had three previous accounts on TikTok, all of which have been removed. He often shares cooking videos on his current TikTok account. He posts vlogs, mukbangs and TikToks on his Icy Wyatt YouTube channel, where he has amassed over 20,000 subscribers.

name: Gloria Stuart

name: Elton Castee

name: Tia Mowry
about: Starred opposite her identical twin sister Tamera Mowry on the ABC series Sister, Sister from 1994 to 1999. She then went on to play Melanie Barnett Davis on the comedy/drama series The Game and Stephanie Phillips on the Nickelodeon series Instant Mom. In 2019, she began starring on the Netflix original series Family Reunion.

name: Noah Miller
about: Popular TikTok star who is best known for the comedy and reaction videos he posts to his nmillz1 TikTok account. He has gained over 4.6 million followers on the platform.

name: Sylvester Stallone
about: Director, actor and screenwriter best known for playing Italian-American boxer Rocky Balboa in the 1976 film Rocky. He reprised the role in six sequels, released from 1979 to 2015. He also portrayed John Rambo in the Rambo film franchise and played leading roles in the films Cliffhanger, The Expendables, Cop Land and Spy Kids 3-D: Game Over.

name: Dylan Kingwell

name: George W. Bush
about: 43rd President of the United States who narrowly defeated Al Gore in the 2000 election despite losing the popular vote, then won re-election against John Kerry in 2004. The tragic September 11 terrorist attacks occurred just eight months into his first presidential term and in response, he called for the War on Terror, which ultimately led to wars in Afghanistan and Iraq.

name: Daithi De Nogla

He has also uploaded challenge videos, reaction videos and Pokémon unboxing videos to his account.

name: Tamera Mowry

name: Zion Williamson

name: Courtney Hadwin

name: A1 Bentley

name: RØMA

He then signed with the San Diego Padres in 2019.

name: Sebi Rich

name: Milly Rosso

name: MS Dhoni

name: Shaun McBride

She also won the 2019 World Cup with the team.

about: Beauty and makeup expert who is popular as a blogger and video content creator on her self-titled YouTube channel. She has accumulated over 1.3 million subscribers.

name: Jon Jones
about: UFC fighter and mixed martial artist who became a two-time UFC light heavyweight champion. He also held the interim UFC light heavyweight championship once. In August 2020, he vacated his light heavyweight UFC title to move up to the heavyweight division.

name: Emma Michelle
about: TikTok superstar whose lip sync videos have earned her more than 440,000 followers on her itzemmamichelle account. She has set videos to artists like Noah Cyrus, Zach Clayton, and Alessia Cara. In 2018, she released her debut single "Something More."

name: Chris Kratt
about: Wildlife enthusiast and the creator, writer and producer of Zoboomafoo, Kratts' Creatures, and other popular educational shows.

name: Emma Kaji
about: Famous for her appearances on the popular Ryan's Family Review YouTube channel. She has gained popularity as one of the younger twin sisters of RyanToysReview while appearing in her family's vlogging entries. She also appears on the Kaji Family channel.

name: Naya Mousa
about: TikTok star who has gained fame for posting acting videos, often performing as both male and female characters. She initially gained popularity for her original characters the Ash Twins. Popular creator on TikTok notable for her naya.mousa account, which has amassed over 3.7 million followers.

name: TapWater
about: Family friendly YouTube personality and content creator who is best known for publishing Roblox videos on his self-titled account. He has amassed more than 410,000 subscribers on the platform. He has gained a modest following on his personal tapwater Instagram account.

name: Howard Schultz
about: Businessman who became founder, chairman, and CEO of Starbucks. He also owned the NBA's Seattle SuperSonics from 2002 to 2006.

name: Jinder Mahal
about: Indian-American who became a rising star of the WWE with a feud with Ted DiBiase and a conspiracy to take down Kane.

name: Brooklyn Nikole
about: Model and influencer who is best recognized for having earned representation from Select Models in Atlanta. She is also known for sharing her fashion and modeling-focused photos through Instagram where she has over 300,000 followers.

name: Girlhefunnyaf44
about: Comedy content creator who is recognized for posting outrageous skits on his girlhefunnyaf44 Instagram account. His sense of humor helped him build a fanbase of more than 600,000 followers.

name: Nathalie Boltt
about: South African actress who played the role of Joey Ortlepp in the SABC 3 soap opera Isidingo from 2001 to 2004. She was cast as the villain, Penelope Blossom, on CW's Riverdale.

name: IlluminaHD
about: YouTube star and gamer who is best recognized for his IlluminaHD YouTube channel where he posts Minecraft content. His videos have earned him over 600,000 subscribers on the video platform.

name: Nicola Sturgeon
about: Affiliated with the Scottish National Party, she took office in 2007 as Deputy First Minister of Scotland and became First Minister of Scotland in 2014. She also served as Cabinet Secretary for Health, Infrastructure, and Parliament.

name: Baby Erin
about: Also known as the Princess of Bounce, she became an internet famous rapper before turning the age of 10. She has a well known single called "Basketball" and her "School House Rock" video went viral.

name: Tim Foust
about: Vocalist in the a capella group Home Free who sings bass for the group. He helped Home Free win NBC's The Sing Off. He also has a country album as a solo artist called The Best That I Could Do.

name: Cody Ryle
about: Social media sensation who was named Mr. Georgia 2014, he is most well known for his live broadcasts on YouNow as well as for his popular Twitter and Instagram accounts.

name: Niki Peter
about: TikTok star who has gained popularity on his self-titled channel. His lip-syncs, montages, and close-up dance challenges, often with his horse, have boosted him to more than 9 million likes.

name: Tyler Downs
about: Trending dance content creator who is best known for his tylerdownss TikTok account. His dancing and diving videos have netted him more than 900,000 fans on the platform. He also qualified for the 2021 Olympics.

name: Mason Wallace
about: Adopted child of Jared and Shelly Wallace who would be featured on the family's YouTube channel CRAZY MIDDLES. The channel garnered more than 500,000 subscribers.

name: Brooklyn Gabby
about: Fashion style blogger with over 550,000 fans on TikTok. She became a member of a collaboration group on TikTok called The Muser Mash, back when the app was still called musical.ly.

name: JJ Shurbet
about: Musical artist who is famous for their scruffpuppie YouTube channel, which was formerly known as my last name isn't ice cream. They have gained massive popularity there for their original vocal and acoustic covers of indie songs alongside pop singles.

name: Benn Suede
about: Best known for his time as lead guitarist, songwriter, and backing vocalist for the award-winning post-hardcore band Crown the Empire from 2011 to 2015. He helped the band release albums titled The Fallout and The Resistance: Rise of the Runaways, the latter of which reached #7 on the Billboard Top 200 chart.

name: Nick Ray
about: TikTok star who is known for his acting as well as his cosplay content. He is known for sharing his daily postings which often feature lip synched skits and other comedic content which he shares for his over 1.6 million fans on the app.

name: Tori Assise
about: Vlogger who posts hair, makeup and DIY videos as well as advice videos for other young girls on her self-titled YouTube channel. So far, her channel has earned more than 150,000 subscribers.

name: Nancy Carell
about: Actress and comedian best known for her appearances on Saturday Night Live, The Daily Show, and The Office.

name: Trai Byers
about: Famous for his portrayal of Civil Rights leader James Forman in the 2014 film Selma, Byers is also known for his starring role as Andre on the Fox series Empire. In addition, he played the recurring role of Alec Martin on The CW series 90210.

name: Corbin Cunningham
about: Social media star and content creator who has gained popularity for the comedic, reaction, POV, and dance videos he posts to his c0rbo TikTok account. His videos, which often involve his friends, have earned him over 2.1 million followers on the platform.

name: Mr Eazi
about: Afrobeat singer who broke into the music industry with a single titled "Pipi Dance" and mixtape called About to Blow. He would go on to release tracks titled "Skintight", "Hollup," and "Sample You."

name: LaMarcus Aldridge
about: NBA power forward who played in four straight All-Star games with the Portland Trail Blazers from 2012 to 2015. He spent his first nine NBA seasons in Portland, then signed with the San Antonio Spurs in 2015.

name: Sami Yusuf
about: Middle Eastern musician known for blending East and West styles. His single "Al-Mu`allim," from his debut album of the same name, topped seven million sales worldwide.

name: Hero DW
about: TikTok content creator and personality who rose to fame by posting jump tricks and flips on his herodw account. His stunts have helped him amass more than 5 million fans on the platform.

name: Pop Smoke
about: Brooklyn rapper who immediately cemented himself in the rap scene with viral hits called "Meet the Woo" and "Welcome to the Party." He dropped a mixtape called Meet the Woo Volume 1 in the summer of 2019.

name: Joey Bragg
about: Actor and stand-up comedian who became known for his role as Joey on the Disney Channel's Liv and Maddie. He also starred in Fred 3: Camp Fred in 2012 and in The Outfield in 2015. In 2021, he began starring as Freddie Raines on the ABC series Call Your Mother.

name: Jaclyn Hill
about: Professional makeup artist, beauty and fashion blogger, and YouTube phenomenon who publishes videos to her channel Jaclynhill1. She has also run her own beauty company called Jaclyn Hill Cosmetics.

name: SAS-ASMR
about: With more than 2.5 billion total video views, SAS became a YouTube phenomenon specializing in eating, whispering and mukbang ASMR content. Two of her most popular videos featured her eating raw honeycomb.

name: Abby Rao
about: Model and Instagram star who is known for sharing a range of modeling shots in swimwear and beach wear. She is also an ambassador for Fashion Nova and shares her modeling shots through Instagram for her over 2.4 million followers.

name: Julianne Hough
about: Rose to fame as a pro dancer on ABC's Dancing with the Stars, starred in the 2011 film Footloose, and released an award-winning album that hit #1 on the Billboard Country charts. She portrayed Sandy in the 2016 Fox broadcast of Grease Live! In 2019, she became a judge on America's Got Talent.

name: Corl
about: Specializing in Roblox content, he became a YouTube sensation who earned more than 1.2 million subscribers by posting Roblox Roleplays. He also posted Minecraft Roleplays and what he called "Minecraft Who's Your Daddy" videos. His last video was uploaded in January 2019.

name: Sandra Oh
about: Best known for playing Dr. Cristina Yang on the hit television series Grey's Anatomy, she has also appeared in such films as The Princess Diaries, Sideways and Ramona and Beezus.

name: Melissa Metrano
about: Social media star who is known for specializing in health, yoga, and beauty related content. She is also the founder of MelsFit which offers seminars on a variety of wellness related fields including yoga, personal training, and barre instruction. She shares her health and fitness related content through Instagram where she has over 340,000 followers. She also uploads DIY videos on her melissametrano TikTok account with more than 7 million followers.

name: Julian Jara
about: One half of the content-creating social media duo and music group known as 99 GoonSquad. He and his twin brother Jovani have over 220,000 subscribers on their 99 GoonSquad YouTube channel, where they've posted a range of fun and comical videos, often reacting to current trends or events. They have released songs titled "Got It Bad" and "Next To Me."

name: Ben Simmons
about: Australian basketball player who was selected first overall in the 2016 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia 76ers after spending one year playing college basketball at LSU. He was named the NBA Rookie of the Year in 2018.

name: Alycia Debnam-Carey
about: After rising to fame on the reality series Next Stop Hollywood, she had a recurring role on The CW series The 100 and played significant roles in the films Into the Storm and The Devil's Hand.

name: Gisele Bündchen
about: International super model and former Victoria's Secret Angel who has graced the covers of Vogue. She became the highest-paid model in the fashion industry in 2004.

name: Elle Walker
about: Initially finding success with her YouTube channel whatsupelle, she gained an even bigger following through her second channel WhatsUpMoms, amassing over 3.3 million subscribers. Their channel has given useful information for mothers all across America to help them with their everyday lives.

name: Liv Shumbres
about: Talented tumbler who gained fame for appearing in multiple MattyB music videos including "My Oh My" and "Crush on You." She has also been featured in several MattyB vlogs and challenges like "Whipped Cream Challenge." She has promoted for the BEAM supplements company on her Instagram and has been an official BEAM sponsored athlete.

name: Jovani Jara
about: Widely known as one-half of the popular content-creating social media duo and music group known as 99 GoonSquad alongside his twin brother Julian. The brothers gained followings on several social media platforms, particularly YouTube, where they post commentaries, challenges and other fun videos. In 2015, they produced the song "Younow Gurl" and they have released other singles titled "Got It Bad" and "Gucci Girlfriend" as well.

name: Nella Rose
about: YouTube vlogger who has accumulated more than 650,000 subscribers on her self-titled channel. She is known for creating challenges, stories, lookbooks, and various vlogs. She has been featured on BET, Netflix, and BBC.

name: Alyssa Howard
about: Popular social media star and content creator best recognized for her self-titled YouTube channel, where she posts vlog, fashion and beauty videos. She has accumulated over 250,000 subscribers on the platform. She has also sold her own t-shirts and hoodies on her Alyssa Howard Shop website.

name: Mia Feldman
about: Older sister of former YouTube vlogger and beauty guru CloeCouture.

name: Natalie Wood
about: Actress who played Maria in West Side Story in 1961 and won a Golden Globe Award for her role in the 1979 remake of From Here to Eternity. As a teenager, she was nominated for an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for her work in Rebel Without a Cause.

name: Paige Hurd
about: Actress who played Tasha Clarkson on The CW's series Everybody Hates Chris from 2006 to 2009. She became a regular on the show City 17 Street in 2014 and in 2019, she began starring on The Oval.

name: Michael Yerger
about: Real estate agent most famous for being a contestant on Survivor: Ghost Island. He is also an underwear model who has been represented by the LA Models, Ford Models and Kult Models agencies.

name: Chris Cornell
about: Singer with Soundgarden, the group known for songs like "Black Hole Sun" and "Rusty Cage," who was also a successful solo artist and the frontman for Audioslave.

name: Manjul Khattar
about: TikTok creator notable for doing lip sync duets for his more than 13 million fans on the account manjullll. He earned the verification crown as well as badges for top comedian and top style guru on TikTok.

name: Ledger Nelson
about: 2019 addition to the popular Nelson family that found fame on the YouTube channel Not Enough Nelsons.

name: Ray Allen
about: NBA sharp shooter who spent the first 7 seasons of his career with the Milwaukee Bucks, then four with the Seattle Supersonics. He helped lead the Boston Celtics to an NBA Championship in 2008 and was a key member of the 2013 NBA Champion Miami Heat.

name: Anton du Beke
about: Professional dancer who was on the popular British TV show Strictly Come Dancing and presented the UK show Hole in the Wall.

name: ZaZa Maree
about: Singer and songwriter known for her live performances across the United States and for the 2013 EP #Forever. She has become particularly known for the singles "Just Fine" and "Go Back."

name: Naii.elyy
about: Dance and POV-style skit content creator who is best known for her self-titled TikTok account. She has more than 1.8 million followers on the platform. She is also well-known as the face behind the greenskiiofficial account, and is a member of the hoodskiiz collective.

name: Billy Mays
about: Loud-voiced advertising pitchman for products such as OxiClean.

name: Omar Epps
about: Best known for playing the role of Dr. Eric Foreman on the popular television series House M.D. He previously played a television doctor on ER as well.

name: Lisa Dolan
about: Mother of Vine stars Cameron, Ethan, and Grayson Dolan.

name: Carlos Santana
about: Iconic Mexican guitarist known for fusing Latin sounds with rock as the leader of the band Santana. He's considered the Latin artist with the most record sales in history. His best known songs include "María María," "Smooth," "Corazón Espinado" and "Black Magic Woman."

name: Steven Adams
about: Seven-foot center who made his NBA debut in 2013 with the Oklahoma City Thunder after winning a New Zealand Basketball League title in 2011.

name: Denzel Harris
about: Dancer who is known online under the name SheLovesMeechie. He posts his dance videos to his popular YouTube channel and Instagram account, earning over 480,000 subscribers and 650,000 followers on the platforms, respectively.

name: Jordan Rodrigues
about: Australian actor known for his roles as Christian Reed on Dance Academy and Jai Fernandez on Home and Away. He played the role of Miguel in Lady Bird.

name: Christian Haynes
about: Social media star and content creator who has gained popularity for the comedic skits he posts to his theeblackbadger TikTok account. His videos have earned him over 1.8 million followers on the platform.

name: Terri Irwin
about: American-born naturalist, author, and television personality who was the wife of Steve Irwin, the late Crocodile Hunter. Her wildlife conservation efforts earned her an honorary membership in the Order of Australia. In 2018, her and her family began starring on their own reality series called Crikey! It's the Irwins.

name: Alison Fernandez
about: Actress who rose to fame as a child portraying Zara Amaro in the popular drama Law & Order: Special Victims Unit beginning in 2011. She has also had roles in Netflix's Orange Is the New Black, The CW's Jane the Virgin and Netflix's Team Kaylie. In 2018, she starred as Lex in Life-Size 2 with Tyra Banks.

name: Jay Zwarts
about: Rapper and social media influencer recognized for viral hits such as "Ontwijkt" and "Mijne." He boasts more than 270,000 followers on his private verified Instagram account.

name: John Swift
about: Also known as Jswazz or just Swazz, he has an extremely passionate fanbase on both Twitter and Instagram and is a good friend of Nate Maloley. Also a musician, he has released music on his SoundCloud page.

name: Taryne Renee
about: American social media star popular for the YouTube channel TaryneItUp Vlogs, where she vlogs for more than 20,000 subscribers.

name: Victor Goldstein
about: TikTok personality and point-of-view content creator who rose to fame by sharing dance and lip sync performances on his vctorr_ account.

name: King Science
about: Comedy, meme, and animation content creator who is known for posting short form videos on his verified king.science TikTok account. He has gone on to garner more than 12 million fans and 165 million hearts on the platform.

name: Alexis Simone
about: YouTuber known for her fashion-centric content, often of the vlogging variety. Her self-titled channel has amassed over 60,000 subscribers.

name: Enrique Peña Nieto
about: Mexico's 57th president who began his six year term in 2012, vowing to reinvigorate the country's economy and crack down on the drug wars.

name: Amber Turner
about: Fashion blogger who is widely known for her Ambers Wardrobe page on Depop. She has earned more than 20,000 followers there for her custom merchandise and looks. In 2017, she joined the cast of the hit reality show The Only Way Is Essex.

name: Judy Greer
about: Character actress best known for her roles as Kitty Sanchez on Arrested Development and as Julie in the film The Descendants. She has also appeared in Tomorrowland, Ant-Man, and Jurassic World. In 2018, she joined the cast of Halloween with Jamie Lee Curtis.

name: Maggie Lindemann
about: Singer and social media superstar with more than 5 million Instagram followers and over 490,000 Twitter followers. She is known for hit singles such as "Pretty Girl" and "Couple of Kids." She was also featured in the song "Personal" by The Vamps.

name: Kaylee Halko
about: Social star who was born with a rare, premature aging condition called progeria, which makes her young body age at a faster pace. Her personal Instagram account, where she posts pictures of her day-to-day life, has earned over 180,000 followers.

name: Robin Williams
about: Comedian and actor who won an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role in the 1997 film Good Will Hunting. He also played lead roles in the films Dead Poets Society, Hook, Mrs. Doubtfire, Patch Adams, Jumanji and Good Morning, Vietnam. He voiced the genie in the Aladdin films.

name: Noor Dabash
about: Trending dance and lip sync content creator who rose to fame by posting videos on her noordabashh TikTok account. Her moves have helped her garner more than 6 million followers on the platform. She has also posted makeup and perfume promotional content on her noordabashh Instagram, which has over 300,000 followers.

name: Romeo Santos
about: Bachata singer-songwriter who is the lead singer of the band Aventura. His 2013 hit "Propuesta Indecente" and his 2018 duet with Ozuna, "El Farsante," have each surpassed 1 billion views on YouTube. As a solo artist, he's released albums like Formula, Vol. 1 and Vol. 2, Golden and Utopía.

name: Erling Braut Haaland
about: Norwegian soccer striker who began playing for the Austrian Football Bundesliga club Red Bull Salzburg in 2019. He was named the 2018 Eliteserien Breakthrough Player of the Year and won the Golden Boot Award at the 2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup. He began playing for Borussia Dortmund in 2020.

name: Wisp
about: British video game enthusiast and content creator who found fame after starting his Wisp YouTube channel. He has posted gameplay recordings, tips and tricks related to Minecraft for more than 4.4 million subscribers. He has also posted videos of himself playing both mini-games and survival games on Minecraft.

name: Jasmine Cephas Jones
about: Television and stage actress who rocketed to fame starring as Maria Reynolds and Margarita "Peggy" Schuyler Van Rensselaer in the award winning musical Hamilton. She also starred in the 2018 film Blindspotting.

name: Yolanda Gampp
about: Self-taught cake artist who created the popular instructional YouTube channel How To Cake It. She also released a cookbook of the same name and was part of the cast of the Food Network's Sugar Stars. Her cakes have often featured festive designs.

name: Chrishell Stause
about: Actress best known for playing Amanda Dillon on All My Children, and later Jordan Ridgeway in Days of Our Lives. In 2019, she began starring on Netflix's Selling Sunset as the new agent in town.

name: King Roscoe
about: Burgeoning rapper who first rose to fame after appearing on the third season of the Lifetime reality series The Rap Game.

name: Sara Sampaio
about: Portuguese supermodel best known for her work with Victoria's Secret. She has also appeared in GQ, Elle, and Vogue.

name: Diane Guerrero
about: Best known for her role as Maritza Ramos on Netflix's Orange Is the New Black and as Lina on The CW series Jane the Virgin. She also had a recurring role on the third season of Are We There Yet? and starred in DC Universe's Doom Patrol.

name: Scarce
about: YouTuber whose channel has earned over 3.1 million subscribers, mostly through his discussions of news about other YouTubers. His Twitter account also has more than 900,000 followers. He has made videos about David Dobrik, Jake Paul, PewDiePie and others.

name: Paloma Faith
about: Singer turned actress whose debut album spawned five hit singles, including the songs "Stone Cold Sober" and "New York." In 2016 she became a judge on The Voice UK and in 2019, she began starring as Bet Sykes in the Batman series Pennyworth.

name: Jessica Barden
about: English actress best known for playing the role of Kayleigh Morton on the soap opera Coronation Street. She would go on to co-star in the Channel 4 series The End of the F***ing World alongside Alex Lawther. Other film appearances of hers include The Chase and No Angles.

name: Edwin Castro
about: American FIFA gamer on YouTube and a partner with the live streaming service Twitch who is known online as Castro1021. He has earned more than 3.3 million Twitch followers and over 1.9 million YouTube subscribers.

name: Moneeb Kassimi
about: Verified TikTok personality and digital content creator who rose to fame by sharing interesting facts about people and unexplained phenomena. He has more than 4 million followers on his themelomoon account.

name: Alexis Rose
about: Social media personality and dancer known for posting cheerleading and dance videos. She has acquired over 250,000 followers on her self-titled alexisrose_7 Instagram account.

name: Choi Jisu
about: Stage name Lia, she makes up one-fifth of the K-pop group ITZY. The group was formed under JYP Entertainment.

name: Kyle Hanagami
about: Acclaimed dancer/choreographer with credits that include The X Factor (US), Sing Your Face Off, and Nickelodeon's How to Rock, he has also established an enormous presence on his YouTube channel. He received the Industry Dance Award for best class at Los Angeles' three top dance studios.

name: Pearl Grace Dela Paz
about: TikTok star who became best recognized for her text-based videos which often offered commentary on her life. She shared her content with over 2.1 million fans on her channel pearldelapaz. She also became known for posting viral dance videos and a variety of other experimental skits that she filmed in her room which helped her earn over 117 million total likes.

name: TwiistedPandora
about: YouTuber who gained a subscriber base primarily through his Minecraft videos. He is known by his fans for creating series like "Skywars" and "Speed UHC." He later began focusing on Roblox content.

name: Jentezen Franklin
about: Known for such bestselling books as Right People, Right Place, Right Plan and the Fasting series, this Christian author and Pentecostal pastor led the congregations of both the Georgia and California branches of the Free Chapel ministry.

name: Abigail Aguilar
about: Mommy vlogger behind the YouTube channel Life as a Mommy, which has earned more than 460,000 subscribers. The channel is home to clothing hauls, family vlogs, tags, and more.

name: Sammie Lewis
about: Creator on the platform TikTok who became well known for her tea videos that have gained millions of views per videos. They started a trend on TikTok, and have helped her to more than 2.8 million fans.

name: Rebecca Ferguson
about: British pop singer who was a runner-up on The X Factor (UK). She was later offered a record deal with Columbia Records.

name: Josh Hartnett
about: Actor best remembered for his roles in Pearl Harbor and Black Hawk Down. He also appeared in The Virgin Suicides, 40 Days and 40 Nights, and O. From 2014 to 2016, he starred in the horror series Penny Dreadful.

name: Kevin Burgess
about: Christian hip hop artist known by the stage name KB who leads the hip hop group HGA, AKA His Glory Alone. He signed as a solo artist with Reach Records in 2010 and became a member of the record label's hip hop collective 116 Clique.

name: Alexis Carrasco
about: Social media star who gained fame for comprising one-half of the popular Lex & Tati YouTube channel. She ran the channel with her girlfriend at the time, Tatiana Mendoza. They posted various vlogs such as challenges and storytimes before they broke up in early 2020.

name: Nadia Mcbain
about: TikTok star famous for posting dance and lip sync videos. Her nadiamcbain account has gained 950,000 followers and 13 million likes. She went viral in December 2021 with lip sync video that has over 1.3 million views.

name: Tutweezy
about: Social media personality best known as Tutweezy for his standup comedy and funny videos. He has amassed over 800,000 Instagram followers and growing through his comedic content.

name: Edward Herrmann
about: Established actor well-known for his narration of several programs on The History Channel and his performance as Richard Gilmore in Gilmore Girls. He also starred in Eleanor and Franklin and narrated for NOVA.

name: Don Knotts
about: Played the role of Deputy Barney Fife on The Andy Griffith Show. In 1996, he was honored by TV Guide, as they ranked him 27 out of 50 in its Greatest TV Stars of All Time.

name: Filip Dejanovic
about: YouTube star who is widely known for his TheSikrt channel. He has gained popularity there for his original social experiments, pranks, and comedic sketches.

name: DeAndre Jordan
about: NBA shot-blocking and rebounding specialist who led the league in rebounding in 2014 and 2015 as a member of the Los Angeles Clippers. He was also an NBA All-Defensive First Team selection in 2015.

name: Anya Chalotra
about: British-Indian actress notable for her leading roles as Robin Loxley in Sherwood and Yennefer of Vengerberg in The Witcher. She was also previously seen in episodes of The ABC Murders and Wanderlust in 2018.

name: Tewtiy
about: Minecraft YouTuber whose livestreams and mod videos have earned him more than 1.1 million subscribers. Outside of Minecraft, he is also known to frequently post Pixelmon videos.

name: Bobby Briskey
about: Vlogger and freelance videographer/video editor well known for his LivingBobby YouTube channel which surpassed 2.2 million subscribers. He garnered acclaim for his posting content relating to living cheaply in big cities.

name: Holly Tandy
about: Rocketed to fame in 2017 competing on the fourteenth series of The X Factor (UK). She blew the judges away with a cover of "If I Ain't Got You" by Alicia Keys.

name: Kayleigh Mehrtens
about: Social media personality who is famous for her self-titled YouTube channel. She has gained popularity there for her personal vlogging.

name: Sofia Franklyn
about: Online personality who co-hosted the podcast Call Her Daddy, presented by Barstool Sports. She is extremely popular on Instagram with over 800,000 followers.

name: Ernest Hemingway
about: American modernist author whose most famous works include The Old Man and the Sea, A Farewell to Arms, and For Whom the Bell Tolls. A Nobel Prize-winning author associated with the "Lost Generation," Hemingway became known for both his adventurous lifestyle and his eloquently sparse literary aesthetic.

name: Yasmin Kavari
about: Persian YouTuber who's earned a subscriber base of more than 190,000 by uploading a mix of vlogs and makeup and hair tutorials. Her videos have been collectively viewed more than 6 million times.

name: Peter Knetter
about: YouTube star who is widely known for his self-titled channel's content. He has gained popularity there for his gaming Let's Plays and playthroughs, reviews, and commentary, including for Sonic the Hedgehog and Undertale.

name: Cat Stevens
about: Folk singer-songwriter who wrote and performed songs like "The First Cut is the Deepest," "Where Do the Children Play?," and "Wild World."

name: Juno Temple
about: Child actress turned rising star who gained fame for her roles in Atonement and The Dark Knight Rises. Her other credits include Afternoon Delight, Maleficent, and The Other Boleyn Child. In 2018, she began starring as Veronica in Bravo's Dirty John.

name: Jeff Fatt
about: Children's entertainer with The Wiggles and The Cockroaches who received an ARIA Hall of Fame Award in 2011.

name: Selena Gomez
about: Rose to fame for her starring role as Alex Russo on Disney's Wizards of Waverly Place. In 2008, she formed the band Selena Gomez & the Scene. She released three hit albums with the band, then embarked upon her solo career. Her first two solo albums, Stars Dance (2013) and Revival (2015), hit #1 on the U.S. Billboard chart.

name: Larray
about: Social media personality and comedian known online by the persona Larray. He has over 8 million subscribers on his YouTube channel, where he posts a range of comedic videos, occasionally involving video games such as Roblox. He released the original song "First Place" in February 2018. He became a member of the popular TikTok collective Hype House. His full name is Larri Merritt.

name: Madison Pettis
about: Actress who gained recognition as Sophie Martinez on Cory in the House, and played a football star's long-lost daughter in the 2007 film The Game Plan. She received additional fame for her roles in Jake and The Never Land Pirates and Life with Boys. She also voiced Brigitte in the Disney Junior series Fancy Nancy.

name: Lizzy Wurst
about: Instagram and YouTube star, she also gained popularity on Vine before the app was shut down. She has more than 1.5 million Instagram followers and 1.3 million YouTube subscribers.

name: Willem Dafoe
about: Actor who became known for playing bizarre roles in The Boondock Saints, Wild at Heart, and The Hunter. His role as Norman Osborn and the Green Goblin in the 2002 film Spider-Man earned him an MTV Movie Award nomination for Best Villain.

name: Keegan Allen
about: American television actor best known for playing the role of Toby Cavanaugh on ABC Family's popular television show Pretty Little Liars.

name: Hannah Mae Dugmore
about: Best known for her video creations on the app TikTok under the username hmddancer722, she is also a dancer with the South Florida Dance Company. She has over 4.3 million fans on TikTok. She has won several contests on the app and her videos have earned shoutouts from Sia and Daddy Yankee.

name: Prince George
about: First son of Prince William and Catherine Middleton and the third in line to the throne after Queen Elizabeth II, his grandfather, and his father. about: British actor best known for his role as Vernon Dursley, Harry's mean-spirited uncle, in the Harry Potter film franchise. He also starred as Barry Nottingham in Disney's Bedtime Stories.

name: Mia Stammer
about: Japanese-American YouTube fashion and beauty blogger whose hair-coloring videos have earned her over 4.2 million subscribers. She's also widely popular on Instagram with over 1.5 million followers. She has also been known as Mia Sayoko.

name: Delina Hillock
about: Best known for making up one half of the popular YouTube channel SBF TV with her older brother Ian Griffin. The challenges, vlogs and family fun the two siblings upload have garnered them 550,000 subscribers and 61 million views.

name: Jason Momoa
about: Film and television actor who became known to audiences as Khal Drogo in the hit HBO series Game of Thrones. He played Ronon Dex on Stargate: Atlantis from 2005 to 2009. He portrays Aquaman in the DC film universe, debuting in the 2016 film Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice, followed by Justice League and Aquaman.

name: Malcom Suarez
about: TikTok star who rose to fame for his tiobandz channel. He garnered huge popularity for his dubs, dancing skits, and lip syncs.

name: Leon Thomas III
about: He gained fame for his role as Andre Harris on Nickelodeon's Victorious, and appeared in the iCarly crossover episode "iParty with Victorious."

name: Lil Loaded
about: Rapper who is best known for songs such as "6locc 6a6y" and "6acc On The 6locc." In late 2019, he released a music video for his song "Out My Body" which garnered over 600,000 views in just over a week.

name: Casey Barker
about: Rising YouTuber specializing in comedy vlogs and challenges who is also popular on Instagram, Twitter and Snapchat. His caaseybarker Instagram has featured mostly photos of him with his children.

name: Christopher Sturniolo
about: Lip-sync and comedy variety content creator on TikTok best known for his christophersturniolo account. He has gained more than 490,000 followers on the platform. He has also taken part in the Sturniolo Triplets YouTube channel with his brothers. The channel has featured vlogs, challenges and Q&A's.

name: Granny Smith
about: Widely known for being social media star Ross Smith's grandmother and frequent collaborator. She initially appeared on his Vine account, before moving to Instagram. She has been known for her young and raunchy sense of humor and her willingness to do comedic challenges.

name: Anderson Webb
about: Popular as a video content creator under the channel name MRandersonwebb, he is perhaps most well known as the younger brother of YouTube phenomenon Harrison Webb. Some of his most popular videos featured parodies of songs by Harry Styles.

name: Matthew Sturniolo
about: Social media personality and relatable TikTok content creator who rose to fame through the use of his mattsturniolo account. He has more than 220,000 fans on the platform. He has been represented as an influencer by Z Star Digital.

name: Kenza Boutrif
about: Social media star who is widely known for her 6Kenza Instagram account. She has gained popularity there for her selfies and modeling photos. She has been signed by STORM Management for modeling.

name: Weluvche
about: Instagram star also known as Ché who posts comedic videos, pranks and vlogs on his weluvche account. He's worked as a host and influencer and also uses his Instagram following of over 500,000 followers to speak out in support of LGBTQ advocates like him.

name: Eden Skory
about: YouTuber who is known as being a frequent star on vlogs and comedic sketches on The Skorys channel. She often stars in the videos with her three siblings. The sketches have often featured mildly spooky themes that still manage to be family friendly.
